(Ha Na came on the show with her pet parrots.)

243
00:07:58,722 --> 00:08:00,182
(Sparkly eyes)

244
00:08:00,452 --> 00:08:01,822
The transfer process hasn't been completed yet.

245
00:08:02,292 --> 00:08:04,992
(There was an unexpected aspect to Ha Na's pet bird.)

246
00:08:05,292 --> 00:08:08,592
(The dancing bird)

247
00:08:08,732 --> 00:08:10,562
(Its unexpected talent made the whole class dance.)

248
00:08:10,692 --> 00:08:14,462
(The dancing king)

249
00:08:14,632 --> 00:08:17,131
Ha Na, are you uncomfortable around one of us?

250
00:08:17,132 --> 00:08:18,201
Well...

251
00:08:18,202 --> 00:08:19,671
- I bet it's Ho Dong.
- She must be another victim.

252
00:08:19,672 --> 00:08:20,672
- Is it Jang Hoon?
- Who is it?

253
00:08:20,672 --> 00:08:21,672
- Actually...
- It must be...

254
00:08:21,673 --> 00:08:23,211
It's always either Ho Dong or Jang Hoon.

255
00:08:23,212 --> 00:08:25,681
That's right. When I was in elementary school,

256
00:08:25,682 --> 00:08:27,381
I didn't know much about basketball,

257
00:08:27,382 --> 00:08:31,811
but I knew Jang Hoon and Woo Ji Won, who were very famous back then.

258
00:08:31,812 --> 00:08:32,921
- Indeed.
- I knew nothing about basketball...

259
00:08:32,922 --> 00:08:34,521
- when I was in elementary school.
- Right.

260
00:08:34,522 --> 00:08:38,391
All the other kids liked Woo Ji Won.

261
00:08:38,392 --> 00:08:40,491
- But I liked Jang Hoon.
- He was popular.

262
00:08:40,492 --> 00:08:41,761
- Why?
- You were unlike the others.

263
00:08:41,762 --> 00:08:44,131
- I thought he was so fabulous.
- I see.

264
00:08:44,132 --> 00:08:45,861
- You wanted to stand out at school.
- He seemed reliable.

265
00:08:45,862 --> 00:08:47,401
Stand out by being unusual?

266
00:08:47,402 --> 00:08:48,631
- He was my type.
- She wanted to stand out.

267
00:08:48,632 --> 00:08:50,672
- He was your type?
- What did you like about him?

268
00:08:50,872 --> 00:08:52,371
- He's fabulous. That's why.
- I see.

269
00:08:52,372 --> 00:08:54,271
He seemed very reliable, which I liked about him.

270
00:08:54,272 --> 00:08:56,241
- And he was a great player.
- I see that she was a big fan.

271
00:08:56,242 --> 00:09:00,212
But my husband is Jang Hoon's...

272
00:09:00,412 --> 00:09:02,311
- His senior or junior?
- junior by many years.

273
00:09:02,312 --> 00:09:03,681
So he feels a little hard to approach now.

274
00:09:03,682 --> 00:09:05,281
- I can't approach him...
- She's Jang Hoon's victim.

275
00:09:05,282 --> 00:09:06,521
Oh, your husband...

276
00:09:06,522 --> 00:09:07,651
- Is he a basketball player?
- A basketball player.

277
00:09:07,652 --> 00:09:09,022
He's a former basketball player.

278
00:09:09,522 --> 00:09:12,792
- Ha Na's husband...
- Isn't he a coach now?

279
00:09:13,492 --> 00:09:16,132
- His name is Kim Tae Sool.
- Right.

280
00:09:16,632 --> 00:09:18,591
He and I went to the same university.

281
00:09:18,592 --> 00:09:21,131
He also played as a national team player.

282
00:09:21,132 --> 00:09:23,471
Until recently, he was the head coach of a pro team.

283
00:09:23,472 --> 00:09:24,801
He's amazing.

284
00:09:24,802 --> 00:09:26,441
- Have you ever played with him?
- That's right.

285
00:09:26,442 --> 00:09:29,041
We played together when we were on the national team.

286
00:09:29,042 --> 00:09:30,811
We played together on the same team.

287
00:09:30,812 --> 00:09:32,712
He's your favorite junior athlete, right?

288
00:09:33,512 --> 00:09:34,542
Well...

289
00:09:35,982 --> 00:09:37,682
- Well... I...
- He can't answer right away.

290
00:09:38,682 --> 00:09:41,051
- I adore my junior athletes...
- He might not like her husband.

291
00:09:41,052 --> 00:09:43,891
I adore all of my junior athletes.

292
00:09:43,892 --> 00:09:46,062
But Tae Sool and I have a big gap.

293
00:09:46,462 --> 00:09:48,561
- He's his senior by many years.
- You mean, he enrolled later?

294
00:09:48,562 --> 00:09:49,891
- I enrolled ten years before him.
- Oh, ten years?

295
00:09:49,892 --> 00:09:51,592
- I thought he meant an ability gap.
- Yes, ten years.

296
00:09:52,062 --> 00:09:53,302
- We have a big gap.
- He must be very young.

297
00:09:53,702 --> 00:09:55,401
Ha Na is now my junior athlete's wife.

298
00:09:55,402 --> 00:09:56,602
(He met his fan again as his junior athlete's wife.)

299
00:09:56,802 --> 00:09:59,202
- You married a basketball player...
- Right.

300
00:09:59,272 --> 00:10:01,242
- while being a fan of Jang Hoon's.
- Oh, that's right.

301
00:10:01,372 --> 00:10:04,042
Right. Because she couldn't have Jang Hoon.

302
00:10:05,242 --> 00:10:06,341
- I didn't realize that.
- Do your husband and Jang Hoon...

303
00:10:06,342 --> 00:10:07,342
have any similarities?

304
00:10:07,343 --> 00:10:08,612
- No, we have no similarities.
- He...

305
00:10:09,252 --> 00:10:11,352
- Please continue, Ha Na.
- They have no similarities.

306
00:10:11,482 --> 00:10:14,552
My husband is reliable like him. Although he has a small physique,

307
00:10:14,722 --> 00:10:17,091
- he's very reliable and honest.
- I see.

308
00:10:17,092 --> 00:10:18,451
Don't just say he has a small physique.

309
00:10:18,452 --> 00:10:20,461
- They might think he's small.
- A man who's small...

310
00:10:20,462 --> 00:10:23,031
- He's smaller than other players.
- Compared to other players.

311
00:10:23,032 --> 00:10:24,061
That's right.

312
00:10:24,062 --> 00:10:25,932
Jeong Soo is a man who's small but reliable.

313
00:10:26,632 --> 00:10:27,762
Me?

314
00:10:28,032 --> 00:10:29,502
- He's small but reliable.
- Don't say such a thing.

315
00:10:30,732 --> 00:10:33,042
- He seems glad to hear it.
- What is that on your finger?

316
00:10:33,172 --> 00:10:34,602
- Did you imitate your wife?
- What is that?

317
00:10:34,772 --> 00:10:36,511
- It's my wedding ring.
- It's my wedding ring.

318
00:10:36,512 --> 00:10:38,142
(Wedding ring)

319
00:10:38,372 --> 00:10:40,341
(Everyone else is showing their wedding rings.)

320
00:10:40,342 --> 00:10:41,811
(Hiding his left hand)

321
00:10:41,812 --> 00:10:43,112
- Lucky, where's your wedding ring?
- He doesn't have it.

322
00:10:43,382 --> 00:10:45,181
Hold on. Lucky, why aren't you wearing your wedding ring?

323
00:10:45,182 --> 00:10:48,181
- I didn't want to show it off.
- It's to survive the marriage.

324
00:10:48,182 --> 00:10:50,191
- It was too heavy to bring here.
- Why are you acting single?

325
00:10:50,192 --> 00:10:51,952
- It's normal to wear it, Lucky.
- He always leaves it at home?

326
00:10:52,222 --> 00:10:53,922
- Maybe because I just got married, - Yes.

327
00:10:54,062 --> 00:10:55,631
- I still feel a little...
- Uncomfortable?

328
00:10:55,632 --> 00:10:58,091
- I'm not used to wearing a ring.
- It must feel awkward.

329
00:10:58,092 --> 00:10:59,901
I forgot to bring it as I left home in a hurry.

330
00:10:59,902 --> 00:11:03,001
Maybe it's because we know that you got married recently.

331
00:11:03,002 --> 00:11:04,572
You look unusually happy.

332
00:11:05,432 --> 00:11:08,802
Of course, I'm happy. I married a Korean woman,

333
00:11:08,942 --> 00:11:10,742
which is really great.

334
00:11:11,072 --> 00:11:12,611
Before getting married, I was often asked...

335
00:11:12,612 --> 00:11:14,081
- whom I wanted to marry.
- Right.

336
00:11:14,082 --> 00:11:16,082
Whether I wanted to marry an Indian woman or not.

337
00:11:16,152 --> 00:11:17,581
And many people told me that if I married a Korean woman,

338
00:11:17,582 --> 00:11:19,852
- I would become very lucky.
- I see.

339
00:11:20,652 --> 00:11:23,352
- I married one, and I'm so happy.
- Really?

340
00:11:23,452 --> 00:11:25,992
I've been living in Korea for 30 years.

341
00:11:26,192 --> 00:11:27,562
But on every TV show I went on,

342
00:11:27,792 --> 00:11:29,731
I sat next to another foreigner.

343
00:11:29,732 --> 00:11:31,591
- A foreigner special.
- Surrounded by foreigners.

344
00:11:31,592 --> 00:11:32,731
A special episode with people from various countries.

345
00:11:32,732 --> 00:11:35,232
I've never been invited to a show with Korean guests before.

346
00:11:35,872 --> 00:11:37,731
- This is not a foreigner special.
- Exactly.

347
00:11:37,732 --> 00:11:38,771
- Oh, really?
- It's his first time.

348
00:11:38,772 --> 00:11:41,171
- I was lucky to marry her.
- That's true.

349
00:11:41,172 --> 00:11:42,711
Or else, I'd be on shows...

350
00:11:42,712 --> 00:11:44,241
- only on national holidays.
- I didn't realize that until now.

351
00:11:44,242 --> 00:11:45,612
- That's right.
- With some other foreigners.

352
00:11:45,742 --> 00:11:47,542
- That's...
- If you marry a Korean woman,

353
00:11:47,842 --> 00:11:49,081
can you achieve Korean citizenship?

354
00:11:49,082 --> 00:11:52,082
Yes, I can. It was given right after marriage before.

355
00:11:52,252 --> 00:11:54,881
- But some people used the system.
- Some people abused it.

356
00:11:54,882 --> 00:11:57,251
So now you can start the process of achieving it...

357
00:11:57,252 --> 00:11:58,822
after you stay married for several years.

358
00:11:59,692 --> 00:12:01,162
- Did you register your marriage?
- It's complicated.

359
00:12:01,422 --> 00:12:02,532
- Me?
- Yes.

360
00:12:02,892 --> 00:12:05,291
- It seemed quite hard.
- You didn't register your marriage?

361
00:12:05,292 --> 00:12:07,732
The rules... I mean, I want to. I visited the local district office.

362
00:12:08,162 --> 00:12:09,832
But since it's an international marriage,

363
00:12:09,932 --> 00:12:13,372
we must submit documents issued from both countries.

364
00:12:13,902 --> 00:12:16,312
- I was given a list of documents.
- Why is it so complicated?

365
00:12:16,672 --> 00:12:18,071
And it'll take me some time to prepare all those documents.

366
00:12:18,072 --> 00:12:19,511
- So you can't do it right away.
- That's right.

367
00:12:19,512 --> 00:12:21,211
- Even though it takes time, - I guess it takes time.

368
00:12:21,212 --> 00:12:24,352
If you had the will to register your marriage soon,

369
00:12:24,512 --> 00:12:26,821
- I definitely do.
- you would've hurried...

370
00:12:26,822 --> 00:12:28,852
to get those documents from India.

371
00:12:29,092 --> 00:12:31,151
You know, questioning things like that...

372
00:12:31,152 --> 00:12:33,822
often causes a fight between a married couple.

373
00:12:34,362 --> 00:12:36,262
- I advise you to be careful.
- That's not true.

374
00:12:36,792 --> 00:12:38,531
- You see...
- We're here to let you know...

375
00:12:38,532 --> 00:12:40,232
how happy a marriage can be.

376
00:12:40,402 --> 00:12:41,431
- Many people...
- Okay.

377
00:12:41,432 --> 00:12:43,332
- Submit your transfer form first.
- Submit your transfer form.

378
00:12:43,472 --> 00:12:44,731
- And do it in an unusual way.
- The transfer form...

379
00:12:44,732 --> 00:12:47,171
Throw it like a wedding bouquet at Yeong Cheol.

380
00:12:47,172 --> 00:12:49,512
- Right.
- Yeong Cheol or Hee Chul.

381
00:12:49,842 --> 00:12:51,111
- I...
- Right. Throw it backward.

382
00:12:51,112 --> 00:12:53,481
I didn't get a chance to throw the bouquet at my wedding.

383
00:12:53,482 --> 00:12:56,151
- Why?
- My husband did it instead of me.

384
00:12:56,152 --> 00:12:57,251
- Really?
- I see.

385
00:12:57,252 --> 00:12:59,081
- The groom threw the bouquet?
- I'll throw it now.

386
00:12:59,082 --> 00:13:00,681
- These days, at a wedding...
- Can I receive it?

387
00:13:00,682 --> 00:13:01,751
- The groom throws it?
- Yes.

388
00:13:01,752 --> 00:13:02,891
Whichever of the two wants to throw it throws the bouquet.

389
00:13:02,892 --> 00:13:06,162
(It's flying toward Yeong Cheol who doesn't even have a girlfriend.)

390
00:13:06,622 --> 00:13:09,191
(Yeong Cheol has never kissed a girl before.)

391
00:13:09,192 --> 00:13:12,092
(He has only been in unrequited love.)

392
00:13:12,332 --> 00:13:13,462
(I had romantic feelings...)

393
00:13:13,962 --> 00:13:15,532
(for Hwang Bo.)

394
00:13:15,732 --> 00:13:18,432
(He specializes in belated love confession.)

395
00:13:18,832 --> 00:13:21,841
(He missed the right time to confess his feelings many times.)

396
00:13:21,842 --> 00:13:24,442
(He, who's never dated anyone, expresses himself too late.)

397
00:13:24,872 --> 00:13:27,542
(He had an one-sided crush on so many girls in his life.)

398
00:13:28,382 --> 00:13:31,581
(Will the right woman for Yeong Cheol appear this year?)

399
00:13:31,582 --> 00:13:32,681
He missed it.

400
00:13:32,682 --> 00:13:33,982
(Will the right woman for Yeong Cheol appear this year?)

401
00:13:35,082 --> 00:13:36,191
He missed it.

402
00:13:36,192 --> 00:13:37,752
(Catching)

403
00:13:38,152 --> 00:13:39,221
(Darling, you're here.)

404
00:13:39,222 --> 00:13:41,392
- I hope to hear good news soon.
- Exactly.

405
00:13:41,492 --> 00:13:43,591
- He should get married this year.
- He should get married this year.

406
00:13:43,592 --> 00:13:45,731
- We'll look forward to it.
- We'll look forward to good news.

407
00:13:45,732 --> 00:13:48,061
- Right.
- You should be next.

408
00:13:48,062 --> 00:13:49,231
I might actually get married.

409
00:13:49,232 --> 00:13:50,232
- I might get married this year.
- The transfer form...

410
00:13:50,232 --> 00:13:51,232
to Men on a Mission.

411
00:13:51,233 --> 00:13:52,841
Names, Yoon Jeong Soo, Lucky,

412
00:13:52,842 --> 00:13:54,442
Park Ha Na, and Nam Bo Ra.

413
00:13:54,942 --> 00:13:56,071
Welcome!

414
00:13:56,072 --> 00:13:57,342
Thank you all so much.

415
00:13:58,112 --> 00:14:01,581
First, we'll find out how they met their partners.

416
00:14:01,582 --> 00:14:02,982
That's what's written here.

417
00:14:03,082 --> 00:14:04,911
First up is Jeong Soo. He wrote that...

418
00:14:04,912 --> 00:14:06,751
- he'd known her for ten years.
- Exactly.

419
00:14:06,752 --> 00:14:09,751
- You've known her for ten years?
- Yes.

420
00:14:09,752 --> 00:14:12,122
I met her on a TV show ten years ago.

421
00:14:12,722 --> 00:14:16,062
She appeared on the show as a guest.

422
00:14:16,632 --> 00:14:19,032
We contacted each other from time to time.

423
00:14:19,232 --> 00:14:20,901
And recently, we moved our relationship...

424
00:14:20,902 --> 00:14:22,831
- to the next level.
- You moved it forward?

425
00:14:22,832 --> 00:14:25,001
Which one of you continued to contact the other?

426
00:14:25,002 --> 00:14:27,202
- Although they had been friends...
- Does it matter?

427
00:14:27,702 --> 00:14:29,441
- It matters.
- In order for a man and a woman...

428
00:14:29,442 --> 00:14:31,171
to maintain the acquaintance for over ten years,

429
00:14:31,172 --> 00:14:32,911
one of them should make a persistent effort.

430
00:14:32,912 --> 00:14:34,411
- You should have romantic feelings.
- One of them should...

431
00:14:34,412 --> 00:14:35,751
- That's right.
- make an effort.

432
00:14:35,752 --> 00:14:38,282
- Who was the one to reach out?
- To maintain the relationship.

433
00:14:38,682 --> 00:14:40,151
- Was it you, Jeong Soo?
- It was me.

434
00:14:40,152 --> 00:14:41,221
- Of course, it was Jeong Soo.
- I...

435
00:14:41,222 --> 00:14:43,692
I guess Jeong Soo had feelings for her even ten years ago.

436
00:14:44,122 --> 00:14:46,062
- Is that true?
- I flirted with her ten years ago.

437
00:14:46,192 --> 00:14:48,422
- But it didn't go well.
- Right. It didn't go well then.

438
00:14:48,922 --> 00:14:52,262
Six or seven years later,

439
00:14:52,832 --> 00:14:56,032
I contacted her to inquire after her.

440
00:14:56,332 --> 00:14:57,701
After some time, by accident...

441
00:14:57,702 --> 00:14:59,201
It's funny to call it an accident.

442
00:14:59,202 --> 00:15:01,902
But I saw her name on my phone by accident...

443
00:15:02,342 --> 00:15:04,411
when I entered an initial letter to find someone else's number.

444
00:15:04,412 --> 00:15:06,841
I wondered how she had been doing.

445
00:15:06,842 --> 00:15:08,342
So I contacted her.

446
00:15:08,842 --> 00:15:12,522
She said, "If you want to know, why don't you treat me to a meal?"

447
00:15:12,652 --> 00:15:13,652
(The moment the reciprocal relationship began!)

448
00:15:13,653 --> 00:15:15,182
That's how we met again and...

449
00:15:15,422 --> 00:15:17,522
Holding onto the acquaintance...

450
00:15:17,752 --> 00:15:19,222
- is the key to the success.
- That's right.

451
00:15:19,822 --> 00:15:22,791
- He came here in February, 2025.
- Yes, I did.

452
00:15:22,792 --> 00:15:24,432
I still remember this clearly.

453
00:15:24,632 --> 00:15:26,761
You said you were not seeing anyone at the time.

454
00:15:26,762 --> 00:15:28,161
- He said he had no girlfriend.
- That's right.

455
00:15:28,162 --> 00:15:30,001
It wasn't that I denied our relationship,

456
00:15:30,002 --> 00:15:33,771
but I was unsure if I could maintain the relationship with her.

457
00:15:33,772 --> 00:15:36,011
- You were not sure about it.
- That's what I was thinking.

458
00:15:36,012 --> 00:15:38,911
- Were you seeing her at the time?
- I did keep in touch with her.

459
00:15:38,912 --> 00:15:41,411
- Jeong Soo didn't look his best.
- We didn't call each other often.

460
00:15:41,412 --> 00:15:43,481
- But then...
- So you weren't officially dating.

461
00:15:43,482 --> 00:15:45,052
We started dating officially...

462
00:15:45,582 --> 00:15:48,752
after I recorded the show and before the episode aired.

463
00:15:49,022 --> 00:15:51,392
- That's when we made it official.
- Oh, really?

464
00:15:52,052 --> 00:15:53,762
So we made it official.

465
00:15:53,992 --> 00:15:56,362
- And then the episode aired.
- Since I came on the show...

466
00:15:56,832 --> 00:16:00,231
- We share news with people, right?
- That's right.

467
00:16:00,232 --> 00:16:02,001
So I told her that I had recorded Men on a Mission.

468
00:16:02,002 --> 00:16:03,671
She got so excited for me...

469
00:16:03,672 --> 00:16:05,071
and suggested we should watch it together.

470
00:16:05,072 --> 00:16:06,872
- Did you watch it with her?
- But in the episode, Ho Dong said,

471
00:16:07,102 --> 00:16:10,671
"Apparently, Jeong Soo doesn't have a girlfriend, so..."

472
00:16:10,672 --> 00:16:12,981
- Ho Dong made it clear.
- Yes.

473
00:16:12,982 --> 00:16:14,582
To tell you the truth, Jeong Soo...

474
00:16:14,682 --> 00:16:17,152
(Ho Dong shared a small piece of news.)

475
00:16:17,382 --> 00:16:19,652
(Jeong Soo was afraid of the consequence.)

476
00:16:20,152 --> 00:16:21,752
She got upset and went into the room while watching it with me.

477
00:16:21,922 --> 00:16:23,091
- That's understandable.
- It wasn't official back then.

478
00:16:23,092 --> 00:16:24,152
She went into the room?

479
00:16:24,292 --> 00:16:25,722
- We were in the living room.
- In the same house...

480
00:16:26,022 --> 00:16:27,461
Were you two living together at the time?

481
00:16:27,462 --> 00:16:28,521
No, she came over to my place.

482
00:16:28,522 --> 00:16:29,762
- What?
- Your house...

483
00:16:31,962 --> 00:16:33,562
- Did you move in with her?
- What?

484
00:16:33,902 --> 00:16:36,302
We didn't move in together. Like I said, she came over.

485
00:16:37,872 --> 00:16:39,032
Like I said, she came over.

486
00:16:40,802 --> 00:16:42,101
She came over to my place.

487
00:16:42,102 --> 00:16:43,112
(Don't ask about it anymore.)

488
00:16:43,372 --> 00:16:44,441
(He shows off his wedding ring naturally.)

489
00:16:44,442 --> 00:16:45,881
- I like this pose.
- That was natural.

490
00:16:45,882 --> 00:16:47,241
- I like this pose too.
- That was natural, indeed.

491
00:16:47,242 --> 00:16:48,811
- Because it was a weekend...
- She came over to your house?

492
00:16:48,812 --> 00:16:50,282
She came over to my house.

493
00:16:50,352 --> 00:16:51,511
- That was funny.
- All right.

494
00:16:51,512 --> 00:16:53,022
- Does this show air on Saturdays?
- Yes.

495
00:16:53,152 --> 00:16:54,682
She came over because it was a weekend.

496
00:16:55,682 --> 00:16:58,651
- Lucky's case is similar to his.
- That was funny.

497
00:16:58,652 --> 00:16:59,991
- Lucky?
- Jang Hoon and I...

498
00:16:59,992 --> 00:17:01,092
always talk about this.

499
00:17:01,222 --> 00:17:02,692
- "Eight years of friendship?"
- That's right.

500
00:17:02,792 --> 00:17:05,661
- That's a fake friendship.
- He pretended to be a friend.

501
00:17:05,662 --> 00:17:08,362
- You had feelings for her, right?
- You liked her...

502
00:17:08,902 --> 00:17:10,231
Here's how it all happened.

503
00:17:10,232 --> 00:17:11,771
My wife and I...

504
00:17:11,772 --> 00:17:14,041
became friends first.

505
00:17:14,042 --> 00:17:16,542
When I opened up my restaurant,

506
00:17:16,872 --> 00:17:18,771
many of my acquaintances came.

507
00:17:18,772 --> 00:17:21,681
I had a year-end party with the cast members...

508
00:17:21,682 --> 00:17:24,212
of "Abnormal Summit." And she came as my friend.

509
00:17:24,282 --> 00:17:25,711
We were just friends at the time.

510
00:17:25,712 --> 00:17:28,322
Actually, I had a lot of female friends.

511
00:17:28,852 --> 00:17:30,591
My first impression of her was very good.

512
00:17:30,592 --> 00:17:31,951
She was nice and pretty.

513
00:17:31,952 --> 00:17:34,861
Above all, as she'd lived overseas, she was fluent in English...

514
00:17:34,862 --> 00:17:37,231
and had a different perspective on foreigners.

515
00:17:37,232 --> 00:17:39,902
- I guess she was open-minded.
- Without overseas experience,

516
00:17:40,002 --> 00:17:43,232
you could have prejudiced views on foreigners.

517
00:17:43,672 --> 00:17:46,371
She spoke bluntly, but she had a warm heart.

518
00:17:46,372 --> 00:17:49,442
But it's hard to turn friendship into a romantic relationship.

519
00:17:49,542 --> 00:17:50,841
- Right.
- Right. It's really hard.

520
00:17:50,842 --> 00:17:53,412
Lucky, you kept contacting her, right?

521
00:17:53,642 --> 00:17:56,011
I contacted her once or twice a year...

522
00:17:56,012 --> 00:17:57,381
- when I organized a get-together...
- Oh, really?

523
00:17:57,382 --> 00:17:58,712
At my restaurant...

524
00:17:59,252 --> 00:18:01,452
or when I wanted to see how she was doing.

525
00:18:01,552 --> 00:18:02,951
Since she liked travelling,

526
00:18:02,952 --> 00:18:04,951
I contacted her regarding trivial things.

527
00:18:04,952 --> 00:18:06,192
Since I'm an Indian man...

528
00:18:06,462 --> 00:18:09,222
There are a lot of great quotes from Indian movies, you know.

529
00:18:09,692 --> 00:18:12,031
There's a quote saying, "Fate brings people together."

530
00:18:12,032 --> 00:18:13,101
- Right.
- And...

531
00:18:13,102 --> 00:18:14,262
Although it doesn't apply to everyone,

532
00:18:14,502 --> 00:18:17,232
there's also a quote saying, "You fall in love after marriage."

533
00:18:17,972 --> 00:18:20,572
In Indian movies I watched as a little boy,

534
00:18:20,672 --> 00:18:23,171
love between a couple before marriage...

535
00:18:23,172 --> 00:18:25,712
wasn't described explicitly. There were no kissing scenes.

536
00:18:25,982 --> 00:18:28,511
- The last... Yes.
- We don't usually say things like,

537
00:18:28,512 --> 00:18:31,012
"I want to be your boyfriend. We're an item now."

538
00:18:31,082 --> 00:18:32,412
I'm of such a generation.

539
00:18:32,852 --> 00:18:35,451
So I felt too shy to express myself even though I wanted to.

540
00:18:35,452 --> 00:18:37,722
- To tell her how you felt?
- Did you confess your love for her?

541
00:18:37,822 --> 00:18:40,762
It took me a very long time. I did it right before our marriage.

542
00:18:41,222 --> 00:18:43,092
- That's when you asked her out?
- That's how people get married.

543
00:18:43,292 --> 00:18:45,091
- It always happens unexpectedly.
- I mean...

544
00:18:45,092 --> 00:18:46,861
- Exactly.
- You confessed your feelings...

545
00:18:46,862 --> 00:18:48,601
right before you got married...

546
00:18:48,602 --> 00:18:49,701
When you confess your love, you say something like,

547
00:18:49,702 --> 00:18:51,372
- "I love you."
- That's right.

548
00:18:51,572 --> 00:18:53,471
I don't tell my wife...

549
00:18:53,472 --> 00:18:55,771
- that I love her...
- You don't?

550
00:18:55,772 --> 00:18:57,311
I mean, I don't say those three words.

551
00:18:57,312 --> 00:18:58,411
- But...
- You never said those words?

552
00:18:58,412 --> 00:19:00,811
If you never asked her to date you, how would she have known...

553
00:19:00,812 --> 00:19:02,441
- you two were in a relationship?
- Exactly.

554
00:19:02,442 --> 00:19:04,481
If I say it in English... "Read between the lines."

555
00:19:04,482 --> 00:19:06,151
Even if we don't say such things,

556
00:19:06,152 --> 00:19:07,381
- we can feel it.
- That's true.

557
00:19:07,382 --> 00:19:10,452
- Still, you should show your love.
- You just know you're loved.

558
00:19:10,692 --> 00:19:11,821
Korean women like it...

559
00:19:11,822 --> 00:19:13,761
- when their men express their love.
- That's right.

560
00:19:13,762 --> 00:19:15,092
I'll try to do so from now on.

561
00:19:15,192 --> 00:19:17,961
- Right.
- What made you decide to marry her?

562
00:19:17,962 --> 00:19:20,132
How did you make it happen?

563
00:19:20,402 --> 00:19:23,202
This year, I already turned 48 years old.

564
00:19:23,272 --> 00:19:25,372
Indians normally marry early.

565
00:19:25,572 --> 00:19:26,841
I'm considered old to get married,

566
00:19:26,842 --> 00:19:28,971
and my mom kept nagging me to get married.

567
00:19:28,972 --> 00:19:30,241
But she gave up when I reached over 40...

568
00:19:30,242 --> 00:19:31,642
and stopped mentioning it.

569
00:19:31,872 --> 00:19:33,281
In 2025,

570
00:19:33,282 --> 00:19:36,451
I was able to get to know her and get along with her better...

571
00:19:36,452 --> 00:19:38,812
as we cooked together.

572
00:19:38,852 --> 00:19:40,951
Not long ago, when I visited India...

573
00:19:40,952 --> 00:19:43,922
My mom's over 80 now.

574
00:19:43,952 --> 00:19:45,191
For the first time in a while,

575
00:19:45,192 --> 00:19:47,262
she said, "If you get married..."

576
00:19:48,022 --> 00:19:49,691
"and have a child,"

577
00:19:49,692 --> 00:19:51,792
"I might live another ten years."

578
00:19:52,462 --> 00:19:55,831
Saying that for the first time...

579
00:19:55,832 --> 00:19:58,431
made me think...

580
00:19:58,432 --> 00:20:01,102
I should fulfill my duty as her son.

581
00:20:01,202 --> 00:20:03,271
A few days after she said that,

582
00:20:03,272 --> 00:20:04,671
my then-girlfriend got pregnant...

583
00:20:04,672 --> 00:20:05,971
- She did?
- first.

584
00:20:05,972 --> 00:20:07,911
My then-girlfriend got pregnant after I visited India.

585
00:20:07,912 --> 00:20:09,381
(Congratulations.)

586
00:20:09,382 --> 00:20:11,551
- Amazing.
- That's great news.

587
00:20:11,552 --> 00:20:12,651
- You're right.
- Of course,

588
00:20:12,652 --> 00:20:14,351
I'm on cloud nine that I got to marry her.

589
00:20:14,352 --> 00:20:15,721
But even having a child...

590
00:20:15,722 --> 00:20:17,922
- No doubt.
- All has made me really happy.

591
00:20:18,552 --> 00:20:19,961
- You're indeed lucky.
- Nice.

592
00:20:19,962 --> 00:20:21,162
Next is Ha Na.

593
00:20:21,622 --> 00:20:23,561
Ha Na wrote "straight."

594
00:20:23,562 --> 00:20:27,101
My guess is that her husband fell in love with Ha Na...

595
00:20:27,102 --> 00:20:28,662
- Straight on?
- and pushed ahead.

596
00:20:29,202 --> 00:20:31,172
That was what should've happened, but it was me.

597
00:20:31,572 --> 00:20:32,602
- Really?
- You did?

598
00:20:32,972 --> 00:20:34,071
Ha Na is very bright.

599
00:20:34,072 --> 00:20:37,112
I was dying to get married,

600
00:20:37,442 --> 00:20:39,141
and that man got caught in my radar.

601
00:20:39,142 --> 00:20:41,182
I thought, "He's the one."

602
00:20:41,382 --> 00:20:42,481
- So you feel it.
- I...

603
00:20:42,482 --> 00:20:43,782
kept him from going home.

604
00:20:45,252 --> 00:20:47,982
We had a 14-hour date.

605
00:20:48,182 --> 00:20:49,221
On that day?

606
00:20:49,222 --> 00:20:50,351
- Gosh.
- What did you do?

607
00:20:50,352 --> 00:20:51,421
- It wasn't on the day.
- No?

608
00:20:51,422 --> 00:20:53,891
We met while on an overseas trip.

609
00:20:53,892 --> 00:20:55,491
- Really?
- My friends...

610
00:20:55,492 --> 00:20:56,892
have a diver's get-together.

611
00:20:57,032 --> 00:20:59,431
Since my drama had ended,

612
00:20:59,432 --> 00:21:00,432
- I tagged along.
- I see.

613
00:21:00,762 --> 00:21:02,301
The trip was for a few days.

614
00:21:02,302 --> 00:21:05,172
Apparently, to some, it was a breakup trip.

615
00:21:05,472 --> 00:21:08,401
"Why can't men and women get along well?"

616
00:21:08,402 --> 00:21:10,511
"What kind of person is best to get married to?"

617
00:21:10,512 --> 00:21:11,971
"What kind of person do I want?"

618
00:21:11,972 --> 00:21:13,412
As we chatted,

619
00:21:13,612 --> 00:21:15,082
he was...

620
00:21:15,582 --> 00:21:17,911
- The guy...
- the kind of man I was looking for.

621
00:21:17,912 --> 00:21:19,311
- Is that so?
- What's more,

622
00:21:19,312 --> 00:21:21,752
our places were a five-minute walk away.

623
00:21:22,752 --> 00:21:25,691
So we had plenty of time to meet up,

624
00:21:25,692 --> 00:21:27,422
- Yes, countless.
- as well as excuses.

625
00:21:27,462 --> 00:21:28,961
When we returned to Korea,

626
00:21:28,962 --> 00:21:31,461
we played golf together, a shared hobby.

627
00:21:31,462 --> 00:21:32,731
I'd better pick up a hobby.

628
00:21:32,732 --> 00:21:34,432
- Right.
- I kept asking to go golfing.

629
00:21:34,462 --> 00:21:37,002
With that, I kept him to myself for 14 hours.

630
00:21:37,172 --> 00:21:39,401
He hung out with you because he had feelings for you.

631
00:21:39,402 --> 00:21:40,941
- If not, he wouldn't have joined.
- No.

632
00:21:40,942 --> 00:21:42,341
- That's the case, right?
- Yes.

633
00:21:42,342 --> 00:21:44,341
- Did you not ask him out?
- That was good.

634
00:21:44,342 --> 00:21:46,782
- No, we didn't ask each other out.
- What?

635
00:21:46,882 --> 00:21:48,241
You two just knew, right?

636
00:21:48,242 --> 00:21:49,951
After all the dates...

637
00:21:49,952 --> 00:21:52,111
There was a park between our houses.

638
00:21:52,112 --> 00:21:54,751
We were taking a walk, but my feet were hurting like crazy.

639
00:21:54,752 --> 00:21:56,591
So we sat down on a bench.

640
00:21:56,592 --> 00:21:57,852
When I said my feet hurt,

641
00:21:58,092 --> 00:21:59,322
he massaged them.

642
00:21:59,892 --> 00:22:01,321
You two were already clicking.

643
00:22:01,322 --> 00:22:03,891
- He massaged my sweaty feet.
- Did that make your heart flutter?

644
00:22:03,892 --> 00:22:06,301
- What?
- That's a sign that we should date.

645
00:22:06,302 --> 00:22:07,362
- Exactly.
- Right?

646
00:22:07,502 --> 00:22:10,072
Is the day he massaged your feet considered day one?

647
00:22:10,532 --> 00:22:11,532
No.

648
00:22:11,533 --> 00:22:13,441
Our 1st physical touch was day 1.

649
00:22:13,442 --> 00:22:15,271
After hearing your story,

650
00:22:15,272 --> 00:22:17,641
Yeong Cheol will start massaging every woman's feet.

651
00:22:17,642 --> 00:22:19,171
- You can't do it to just anyone.
- What?

652
00:22:19,172 --> 00:22:20,681
- Don't do it to just anyone.
- No.

653
00:22:20,682 --> 00:22:22,811
- I know not to do that.
- Of course.

654
00:22:22,812 --> 00:22:23,882
Come on!

655
00:22:24,252 --> 00:22:25,681
- It depends on the woman.
- I'll try whatever it is...

656
00:22:25,682 --> 00:22:27,121
after hiking.

657
00:22:27,122 --> 00:22:29,421
- He...
- No matter how much...

658
00:22:29,422 --> 00:22:31,192
Hee Chul and Jang Hoon are like...

659
00:22:31,452 --> 00:22:34,392
- Never?
- The two are neat freaks.

660
00:22:34,562 --> 00:22:35,892
Say that the two casually date someone.

661
00:22:36,262 --> 00:22:37,861
You might go to a park...

662
00:22:37,862 --> 00:22:39,632
- or hike with your date, - Yes.

663
00:22:39,662 --> 00:22:41,802
And her feet might hurt.

664
00:22:42,032 --> 00:22:44,972
Like, she either sprains her ankle or is in pain from blisters.

665
00:22:45,672 --> 00:22:46,901
Would you massage her feet?

666
00:22:46,902 --> 00:22:48,441
Jang Hoon would say, "Why did you want to walk..."

667
00:22:48,442 --> 00:22:49,942
- "in the first place?"
- No.

668
00:22:50,072 --> 00:22:53,082
If my date were the one.

669
00:22:53,342 --> 00:22:55,411
If she were my destiny.

670
00:22:55,412 --> 00:22:56,952
- It's before seeing each other.
- Okay.

671
00:22:57,382 --> 00:22:59,052
- Her ankle...
- I'd massage them for three hours.

672
00:23:00,522 --> 00:23:01,522
He has changed.

673
00:23:01,523 --> 00:23:02,621
- With your bare hands?
- I would...

674
00:23:02,622 --> 00:23:03,751
find all her acupuncture points.

675
00:23:03,752 --> 00:23:04,951
Three hours of massage...

676
00:23:04,952 --> 00:23:06,591
- would be boring.
- If Seo Jang Hoon falls in love,

677
00:23:06,592 --> 00:23:08,822
I'm sure he'd even remove dead skin like doctor fish.

678
00:23:09,092 --> 00:23:11,091
- You don't care about the smell?
- No.

679
00:23:11,092 --> 00:23:12,191
If my date is someone...

680
00:23:12,192 --> 00:23:13,901
- I think is the one, - Of course.

681
00:23:13,902 --> 00:23:15,201
I'd do everything she wants.

682
00:23:15,202 --> 00:23:17,231
- It'd be a scandal right away.
- If Hee Chul's girlfriend...

683
00:23:17,232 --> 00:23:18,301
says her feet hurt, he would say,

684
00:23:18,302 --> 00:23:19,642
- "Me too."
- Same here.

685
00:23:20,772 --> 00:23:22,401
- For sure.
- Mine hurts too.

686
00:23:22,402 --> 00:23:23,411
You're spot on.

687
00:23:23,412 --> 00:23:24,641
- Mine.
- My legs are more important.

688
00:23:24,642 --> 00:23:25,711
So massage each other?

689
00:23:25,712 --> 00:23:27,781
If my girlfriend said her feet hurt, I'd say, "Me too."

690
00:23:27,782 --> 00:23:29,281
- Hee Chul is...
- Are you in pain?

691
00:23:29,282 --> 00:23:30,311
- Me too.
- Me too.

692
00:23:30,312 --> 00:23:32,881
- Hilarious.
- Next, Bo Ra wrote...

693
00:23:32,882 --> 00:23:35,182
- Bo Ra.
- "escaped being BS."

694
00:23:35,682 --> 00:23:37,051
- Was she BS?
- Was it because...

695
00:23:37,052 --> 00:23:38,392
you took care of your siblings?

696
00:23:38,592 --> 00:23:40,621
- Right.
- From all the chaos and such?

697
00:23:40,622 --> 00:23:41,891
- No.
- You wouldn't have had the time.

698
00:23:41,892 --> 00:23:43,892
Actually, my husband was BS.

699
00:23:44,092 --> 00:23:46,091
- Your husband?
- Yes, he was BS.

700
00:23:46,092 --> 00:23:47,162
Is he Kim Yeong Cheol?

701
00:23:47,862 --> 00:23:49,461
- Are you BS?
- Of course.

702
00:23:49,462 --> 00:23:50,531
- Isn't it a lie?
- No.

703
00:23:50,532 --> 00:23:51,601
No, I am not BS.

704
00:23:51,602 --> 00:23:52,671
Saying you're BS is a lie.

705
00:23:52,672 --> 00:23:53,672
- BS is...
- Hey, BS.

706
00:23:53,673 --> 00:23:56,102
- I just called him BS.
- How annoying.

707
00:23:56,272 --> 00:23:57,372
No, okay?

708
00:23:57,572 --> 00:23:58,641
Listen.

709
00:23:58,642 --> 00:24:00,011
BS shouldn't lose hope.

710
00:24:00,012 --> 00:24:01,111
You might get married...

711
00:24:01,112 --> 00:24:02,611
- right away.
- I am not BS.

712
00:24:02,612 --> 00:24:04,612
- Bo Ra, that's not...
- What's BS?

713
00:24:04,682 --> 00:24:05,751
- He's denying it.
- Born single.

714
00:24:05,752 --> 00:24:09,052
I've only recently found out the meaning of "BS."

715
00:24:09,322 --> 00:24:11,192
- Since I'm a foreigner, - Yes.

716
00:24:11,822 --> 00:24:12,921
I just figured it out through the nuance.

717
00:24:12,922 --> 00:24:15,592
I thought BS was a person who goes to a motel solo.

718
00:24:15,692 --> 00:24:17,891
- Motel single?
- Motel single?

719
00:24:17,892 --> 00:24:19,461
- Since you're single?
- Come on now.

720
00:24:19,462 --> 00:24:21,431
- For real.
- That's too romantic.

721
00:24:21,432 --> 00:24:22,432
- No.
- Motel single?

722
00:24:22,433 --> 00:24:24,131
- That was what I thought.
- No, you're right.

723
00:24:24,132 --> 00:24:25,501
- You'd go to a motel single.
- Yes.

724
00:24:25,502 --> 00:24:27,371
People who go to motels alone since they're single.

725
00:24:27,372 --> 00:24:28,401
How did you know...

726
00:24:28,402 --> 00:24:29,641
- your husband was BS?
- Yes, how?

727
00:24:29,642 --> 00:24:30,871
He could've lied to you.

728
00:24:30,872 --> 00:24:32,271
I didn't know at first.

729
00:24:32,272 --> 00:24:34,481
I started dating him quite late.

730
00:24:34,482 --> 00:24:37,182
We met for the 1st time when he was 33 years old.

731
00:24:37,212 --> 00:24:39,611
Nobody would think someone around his age...

