- The mediator?

983
00:33:24,742 --> 00:33:27,281
I could say, "This is why the elder said that,"

984
00:33:27,282 --> 00:33:28,641
and things like that.

985
00:33:28,642 --> 00:33:30,011
- That's good.
- That was nice.

986
00:33:30,012 --> 00:33:32,211
- It's fun.
- My family meet-up was fun.

987
00:33:32,212 --> 00:33:34,082
I asked my wife,

988
00:33:34,382 --> 00:33:36,652
"What food do your parents like?"

989
00:33:37,152 --> 00:33:38,291
Since you're a good cook?

990
00:33:38,292 --> 00:33:40,261
- That's important.
- They like duck meat,

991
00:33:40,262 --> 00:33:42,692
so we went to a good Beijing duck place.

992
00:33:42,992 --> 00:33:44,031
- That's expensive.
- Since I like duck too,

993
00:33:44,032 --> 00:33:45,961
- we went there...
- You went there?

994
00:33:45,962 --> 00:33:48,002
For the first meet-up, and I still remember.

995
00:33:48,332 --> 00:33:50,901
My father-in-law spoke to me in English...

996
00:33:50,902 --> 00:33:52,801
as soon as he saw me, since I'm a foreigner.

997
00:33:52,802 --> 00:33:54,041
- Gosh.
- That's cool.

998
00:33:54,042 --> 00:33:55,601
- He's...
- He searched my name online,

999
00:33:55,602 --> 00:33:58,972
and it's "Gupta Abhishek" in Indian,

1000
00:33:59,672 --> 00:34:02,282
so he said, "Hi, nice to meet you, Gupta Abhishek."

1001
00:34:02,512 --> 00:34:04,651
- He said that.
- That's so nice.

1002
00:34:04,652 --> 00:34:06,482
He made me feel so comfortable,

1003
00:34:06,882 --> 00:34:08,451
so I was really thankful.

1004
00:34:08,452 --> 00:34:11,251
From their perspective, sending off their daughter must be really hard,

1005
00:34:11,252 --> 00:34:13,561
especially since I’m a foreigner, they must have been really worried,

1006
00:34:13,562 --> 00:34:14,661
but they took me in really well.

1007
00:34:14,662 --> 00:34:16,092
Now, we speak in Korean,

1008
00:34:16,222 --> 00:34:19,261
so they tell me, "It's like we have another son,"

1009
00:34:19,262 --> 00:34:20,601
so it's really great.

1010
00:34:20,602 --> 00:34:22,232
- That's great.
- That's great.

1011
00:34:22,432 --> 00:34:23,631
How did you propose?

1012
00:34:23,632 --> 00:34:25,471
I heard that...

1013
00:34:25,472 --> 00:34:26,731
it's more common to propose these days.

1014
00:34:26,732 --> 00:34:28,241
- Yes.
- Did you propose..

1015
00:34:28,242 --> 00:34:29,401
And get proposed to?

1016
00:34:29,402 --> 00:34:31,011
- I did.
- Me, too.

1017
00:34:31,012 --> 00:34:32,671
I heard that...

1018
00:34:32,672 --> 00:34:34,681
people just say what they want.

1019
00:34:34,682 --> 00:34:37,881
It could actually be easier.

1020
00:34:37,882 --> 00:34:39,711
Before you get married,

1021
00:34:39,712 --> 00:34:41,481
you ask your friends,

1022
00:34:41,482 --> 00:34:43,921
"How did you do it?"

1023
00:34:43,922 --> 00:34:46,961
Both foreigners and Koreans said the same thing.

1024
00:34:46,962 --> 00:34:50,761
"Lucky, don't do these two things if you want to be criticized..."

1025
00:34:50,762 --> 00:34:52,092
"by your wife for the rest of your life."

1026
00:34:52,392 --> 00:34:54,061
"First is not being with her..."

1027
00:34:54,062 --> 00:34:55,601
- "when she's giving birth,"
- What?

1028
00:34:55,602 --> 00:34:57,331
"and the second is not proposing."

1029
00:34:57,332 --> 00:34:58,931
- It will last forever?
- Then you will be criticized?

1030
00:34:58,932 --> 00:35:01,171
Even if you're together, you will be criticized for life...

1031
00:35:01,172 --> 00:35:03,571
for not doing those things.

1032
00:35:03,572 --> 00:35:04,771
You need to do that, no matter what?

1033
00:35:04,772 --> 00:35:06,271
You need to propose, no matter what.

1034
00:35:06,272 --> 00:35:08,081
If you don't want to be criticized.

1035
00:35:08,082 --> 00:35:10,111
But you're not so affectionate, Lucky.

1036
00:35:10,112 --> 00:35:11,651
Even if I'm not,

1037
00:35:11,652 --> 00:35:14,351
it's important for the woman,

1038
00:35:14,352 --> 00:35:16,522
so I did it a week before our wedding.

1039
00:35:17,192 --> 00:35:19,651
I proposed one week before the wedding.

1040
00:35:19,652 --> 00:35:22,561
When it comes to proposals, foreigners...

1041
00:35:22,562 --> 00:35:24,332
All my friends from "Abnormal Summit" got married.

1042
00:35:24,692 --> 00:35:25,861
But each of them...

1043
00:35:25,862 --> 00:35:27,261
had a different failure story.

1044
00:35:27,262 --> 00:35:29,201
The ring didn't come out before that day,

1045
00:35:29,202 --> 00:35:30,801
- and so many other things.
- Yes.

1046
00:35:30,802 --> 00:35:32,131
- So many things happen.
- Yes.

1047
00:35:32,132 --> 00:35:34,441
So much information came in my brain,

1048
00:35:34,442 --> 00:35:37,372
so I prepared the ring a month in advance.

1049
00:35:37,642 --> 00:35:38,841
I still remember.

1050
00:35:38,842 --> 00:35:40,381
Our wedding was on September 28, and...

1051
00:35:40,382 --> 00:35:41,781
- You got married on September 28?
- Yes.

1052
00:35:41,782 --> 00:35:43,081
- That's my birthday.
- Happy birthday.

1053
00:35:43,082 --> 00:35:44,711
That's so cool.

1054
00:35:44,712 --> 00:35:46,551
- So weird you were born that day.
- You finally knew your birthday.

1055
00:35:46,552 --> 00:35:47,981
That's cool.

1056
00:35:47,982 --> 00:35:50,181
Our wedding was on September 28,

1057
00:35:50,182 --> 00:35:53,691
and I had to propose on September 24.

1058
00:35:53,692 --> 00:35:55,421
- I even begged the jewelry store...
- That's close.

1059
00:35:55,422 --> 00:35:57,161
- That's close.
- to have it ready in the morning.

1060
00:35:57,162 --> 00:36:01,931
I told my wife that my friend had gifted us a yacht ride,

1061
00:36:01,932 --> 00:36:04,171
- so we need to go and ride that.
- That's cool.

1062
00:36:04,172 --> 00:36:06,601
My wife said, "We have so much to prepare."

1063
00:36:06,602 --> 00:36:08,471
"What do you mean, we need to ride a yacht?"

1064
00:36:08,472 --> 00:36:09,701
I said, "No, we need to go."

1065
00:36:09,702 --> 00:36:12,941
I secretly prepared the ring,

1066
00:36:12,942 --> 00:36:14,441
and went to ride the yacht.

1067
00:36:14,442 --> 00:36:16,082
But there was just one day in September...

1068
00:36:16,382 --> 00:36:18,011
when it was raining,

1069
00:36:18,012 --> 00:36:19,212
and it was September 24.

1070
00:36:20,852 --> 00:36:22,082
- It was driving me crazy.
- But you went to ride it?

1071
00:36:22,582 --> 00:36:24,191
Why did it have to rain that day?

1072
00:36:24,192 --> 00:36:25,751
My wife said, "It's raining."

1073
00:36:25,752 --> 00:36:27,921
"Can't we go tomorrow?"

1074
00:36:27,922 --> 00:36:30,021
I had already prepared everything inside the yacht.

1075
00:36:30,022 --> 00:36:31,691
I decorated it all.

1076
00:36:31,692 --> 00:36:34,361
"My friend has other plans for tomorrow,"

1077
00:36:34,362 --> 00:36:36,161
"so it might not be ready tomorrow."

1078
00:36:36,162 --> 00:36:37,731
- "We need to go today, for sure."
- "Let's go."

1079
00:36:37,732 --> 00:36:40,071
We took the umbrella and when we went in,

1080
00:36:40,072 --> 00:36:42,171
I proposed,

1081
00:36:42,172 --> 00:36:44,341
and she loved it.

1082
00:36:44,342 --> 00:36:46,111
- I'm sure she sensed it a bit.
- Your wife...

1083
00:36:46,112 --> 00:36:47,782
would have known on the way.

1084
00:36:48,342 --> 00:36:49,781
She knew, but...

1085
00:36:49,782 --> 00:36:51,411
- she was touched by your effort.
- Yes.

1086
00:36:51,412 --> 00:36:54,251
I think it's helpful for the men...

1087
00:36:54,252 --> 00:36:55,421
when women pretend not to notice...

1088
00:36:55,422 --> 00:36:56,821
- Sure.
- even if they sense something.

1089
00:36:56,822 --> 00:36:58,921
- Sure.
- When you mention a yacht,

1090
00:36:58,922 --> 00:37:00,561
- you can notice.
- Sure.

1091
00:37:00,562 --> 00:37:02,091
- It's a bit too obvious.
- Still...

1092
00:37:02,092 --> 00:37:04,661
Did you also propose, Jeong Soo?

1093
00:37:04,662 --> 00:37:06,091
- I did.
- I only remember you proposing...

1094
00:37:06,092 --> 00:37:09,001
with the seat cushion, like this.

1095
00:37:09,002 --> 00:37:11,701
On Ho Dong's show.

1096
00:37:11,702 --> 00:37:13,631
- That was so long ago.
- With the seat cushion.

1097
00:37:13,632 --> 00:37:16,141
- I know.
- Mine didn't go too well.

1098
00:37:16,142 --> 00:37:17,271
- Did you do it, though?
- Did you fail?

1099
00:37:17,272 --> 00:37:20,112
Yes. I asked my wife out to dinner,

1100
00:37:20,712 --> 00:37:21,981
and at that time,

1101
00:37:21,982 --> 00:37:24,011
I quickly went home to prepare...

1102
00:37:24,012 --> 00:37:26,051
- You prepared it?
- the flowers and champagne.

1103
00:37:26,052 --> 00:37:28,281
I went down, and we had dinner.

1104
00:37:28,282 --> 00:37:29,921
I said, "Go on home, Honey."

1105
00:37:29,922 --> 00:37:32,191
"I will finish this up and follow you."

1106
00:37:32,192 --> 00:37:33,192
She said that she would wait for me,

1107
00:37:33,193 --> 00:37:34,921
but I asked her to go up first.

1108
00:37:34,922 --> 00:37:35,992
She agreed, and said,

1109
00:37:36,392 --> 00:37:39,091
"Do you have a proposal prepared upstairs?"

1110
00:37:39,092 --> 00:37:40,092
- Gosh.
- Gosh.

1111
00:37:40,862 --> 00:37:43,162
(The cursed proposal)

1112
00:37:43,562 --> 00:37:44,871
She was so quick to catch on.

1113
00:37:44,872 --> 00:37:46,331
- Gosh, she's sharp.
- But...

1114
00:37:46,332 --> 00:37:48,371
- But I said...
- That kills the mood.

1115
00:37:48,372 --> 00:37:50,001
I got mad at her then.

1116
00:37:50,002 --> 00:37:51,072
"No way!"

1117
00:37:51,272 --> 00:37:52,911
(That makes her feel even more certain.)

1118
00:37:52,912 --> 00:37:54,741
- His pride.
- "Just go up, already!"

1119
00:37:54,742 --> 00:37:56,011
(The guy proposing snaps back)

1120
00:37:56,012 --> 00:37:57,681
Like the Gangwon Province guy that I am.

1121
00:37:57,682 --> 00:37:59,281
- That's how we are.
- So, she went up.

1122
00:37:59,282 --> 00:38:01,381
- You didn't want to get caught?
- No.

1123
00:38:01,382 --> 00:38:03,481
After 5 to 10 minutes,

1124
00:38:03,482 --> 00:38:05,651
I expected her to be touched like this,

1125
00:38:05,652 --> 00:38:07,051
and I went up to see.

1126
00:38:07,052 --> 00:38:08,561
- I had prepared it on the table.
- Yes.

1127
00:38:08,562 --> 00:38:10,731
But she didn't go to the table,

1128
00:38:10,732 --> 00:38:12,291
and went to the dressing room first,

1129
00:38:12,292 --> 00:38:14,101
and she was tidying up her clothes.

1130
00:38:14,102 --> 00:38:17,001
I went in and was so shocked that I went back out.

1131
00:38:17,002 --> 00:38:19,732
When I went back in, she came out of the dressing room,

1132
00:38:20,032 --> 00:38:21,402
and said, "What's this on the table?"

1133
00:38:21,802 --> 00:38:23,201
That's what she said.

1134
00:38:23,202 --> 00:38:24,271
- There you go.
- Yes.

1135
00:38:24,272 --> 00:38:26,611
"What's this, Jeong Soo? What is this? No way."

1136
00:38:26,612 --> 00:38:28,012
And she wouldn't look at it.

1137
00:38:28,382 --> 00:38:31,082
So I took her in and said,

1138
00:38:31,282 --> 00:38:32,782
"Thank you for marrying me."

1139
00:38:34,182 --> 00:38:36,652
That's how I made her accept it.

1140
00:38:36,952 --> 00:38:38,591
When men propose,

1141
00:38:38,592 --> 00:38:39,951
they all have it prepared...

1142
00:38:39,952 --> 00:38:41,861
- in their head.
- Yes.

1143
00:38:41,862 --> 00:38:43,721
"I will go like this, and then here,"

1144
00:38:43,722 --> 00:38:46,391
"and the weather will be amazing, and I will give the ring."

1145
00:38:46,392 --> 00:38:48,061
But it turns out to be raining...

1146
00:38:48,062 --> 00:38:49,501
- and ruined.
- Yes.

1147
00:38:49,502 --> 00:38:51,031
What about you, Ha Na, did you get proposed to?

1148
00:38:51,032 --> 00:38:52,201
- Or did you do it?
- I received it.

1149
00:38:52,202 --> 00:38:53,202
I wanted to do it, but I received it.

1150
00:38:53,203 --> 00:38:54,302
Was it romantic?

1151
00:38:54,602 --> 00:38:57,672
Romantic? It was a bit dirty.

1152
00:38:57,942 --> 00:38:59,042
- What?
- What?

1153
00:38:59,342 --> 00:39:00,642
(What?)

1154
00:39:00,882 --> 00:39:01,981
What?

1155
00:39:01,982 --> 00:39:03,242
- I'll tell you why.
- What are you talking about?

1156
00:39:03,382 --> 00:39:05,051
Even when we were dating,

1157
00:39:05,052 --> 00:39:07,682
we didn't really keep track of special occasions.

1158
00:39:07,882 --> 00:39:09,321
We even forgot our anniversary and said,

1159
00:39:09,322 --> 00:39:11,522
"It was our 100th day yesterday." That's how we are.

1160
00:39:11,652 --> 00:39:12,991
We're both laid-back.

1161
00:39:12,992 --> 00:39:16,091
So he felt quite pressured about how to propose.

1162
00:39:16,092 --> 00:39:18,192
- Right.
- I didn't want to pressure him.

1163
00:39:18,462 --> 00:39:21,331
Then we joined the marriage program.

1164
00:39:21,332 --> 00:39:23,662
So I had the feeling...

1165
00:39:23,802 --> 00:39:25,201
he'd propose to me during the show.

1166
00:39:25,202 --> 00:39:28,242
When the wedding day approaches, women always anticipate.

1167
00:39:28,602 --> 00:39:30,201
- That's right.
- "Would it be today?"

1168
00:39:30,202 --> 00:39:31,771
- We always have that anticipation.
- That's right.

1169
00:39:31,772 --> 00:39:33,741
You'd get excited even if he said, "Let's go eat."

1170
00:39:33,742 --> 00:39:35,242
- You just get excited somehow.
- That's right.

1171
00:39:35,342 --> 00:39:38,512
He suddenly told me to exercise in the show.

1172
00:39:38,682 --> 00:39:40,181
I used to play soccer,

1173
00:39:40,182 --> 00:39:41,922
so he told me to go to a soccer lesson.

1174
00:39:41,982 --> 00:39:43,582
I tied my hair up,

1175
00:39:43,682 --> 00:39:46,022
and I wore purple shorts.

1176
00:39:46,192 --> 00:39:47,922
I was drenched in sweat.

1177
00:39:48,222 --> 00:39:49,862
Something felt off.

1178
00:39:50,092 --> 00:39:51,632
He told me to go home a bit late.

1179
00:39:52,162 --> 00:39:54,462
"Why? Goodness, this is a disaster."

1180
00:39:54,862 --> 00:39:58,071
I went to the bathroom. The soccer training field...

1181
00:39:58,072 --> 00:40:00,272
had a bathroom. It was indoors.

1182
00:40:00,672 --> 00:40:03,241
- I washed my hair...
- You tried to look pretty.

1183
00:40:03,242 --> 00:40:04,441
- like this.
- Nice.

1184
00:40:04,442 --> 00:40:06,012
I dried my hair like crazy.

1185
00:40:06,212 --> 00:40:08,911
If you watch the show, my hair looks tidy.

1186
00:40:08,912 --> 00:40:10,652
Like this.

1187
00:40:10,882 --> 00:40:12,551
So, I did expect it.

1188
00:40:12,552 --> 00:40:14,082
I came home.

1189
00:40:14,282 --> 00:40:15,581
I wasn't at all surprised,

1190
00:40:15,582 --> 00:40:17,181
but I had to act, since I was an actor.

1191
00:40:17,182 --> 00:40:18,852
But that doesn't really work.

1192
00:40:19,492 --> 00:40:20,692
Really?

1193
00:40:20,862 --> 00:40:23,191
- You had to react.
- Since it wasn't what I wanted.

1194
00:40:23,192 --> 00:40:25,561
- I also wasn't dressed well.
- Goodness.

1195
00:40:25,562 --> 00:40:26,731
- This is funny.
- But I still tried my best.

1196
00:40:26,732 --> 00:40:28,302
I said, "Goodness" and acted amazed.

1197
00:40:28,362 --> 00:40:29,561
But you know the obvious things.

1198
00:40:29,562 --> 00:40:30,971
Everything was so obvious.

1199
00:40:30,972 --> 00:40:33,101
- There was a path of roses.
- It was obvious.

1200
00:40:33,102 --> 00:40:34,171
Don't say it like that.

1201
00:40:34,172 --> 00:40:35,571
- But...
- Is that obvious?

1202
00:40:35,572 --> 00:40:36,801
- It was obvious.
- It feels like...

1203
00:40:36,802 --> 00:40:38,012
she's saying that to me.

1204
00:40:38,212 --> 00:40:40,982
But he wrote something on the floor.

1205
00:40:41,142 --> 00:40:42,411
- That really...
- That's...

1206
00:40:42,412 --> 00:40:44,081
touched me personally.

1207
00:40:44,082 --> 00:40:45,511
You were really touched. You weren't acting.

1208
00:40:45,512 --> 00:40:46,682
I was really touched.

1209
00:40:47,052 --> 00:40:49,451
How did the pure guy propose, Bo Ra?

1210
00:40:49,452 --> 00:40:51,452
He wouldn't know anything about it.

1211
00:40:51,592 --> 00:40:53,291
The pure guy's proposal...

1212
00:40:53,292 --> 00:40:55,891
was just pure.

1213
00:40:55,892 --> 00:40:58,762
So I was really touched.

1214
00:40:58,892 --> 00:41:00,561
- You were touched.
- Yes. I was really touched.

1215
00:41:00,562 --> 00:41:02,301
- Because you like him.
- I didn't expect it.

1216
00:41:02,302 --> 00:41:03,331
How was it?

1217
00:41:03,332 --> 00:41:05,431
- We traveled to Tokyo.
- To Japan.

1218
00:41:05,432 --> 00:41:07,842
(The couple went to Japan 1 year ago.)

1219
00:41:08,202 --> 00:41:10,471
My husband plans most of the trips.

1220
00:41:10,472 --> 00:41:11,971
That was the case then too.

1221
00:41:11,972 --> 00:41:15,042
That day, we went to a restaurant...

1222
00:41:15,342 --> 00:41:17,711
with a view of the Tokyo Tower.

1223
00:41:17,712 --> 00:41:19,551
- It was an outdoor restaurant.
- It would have been so pretty.

1224
00:41:19,552 --> 00:41:21,581
Moreover, the weather was so nice.

1225
00:41:21,582 --> 00:41:23,482
(Even the weather was amazing.)

1226
00:41:23,582 --> 00:41:25,152
(Thanks to the weather)

1227
00:41:25,292 --> 00:41:27,791
So I ate dinner outside...

1228
00:41:27,792 --> 00:41:30,892
and kept saying I was happy.

1229
00:41:31,032 --> 00:41:34,002
My husband said, "I'll go to the bathroom,"

1230
00:41:34,332 --> 00:41:36,261
and I waited for him.

1231
00:41:36,262 --> 00:41:38,272
He came back,

1232
00:41:38,632 --> 00:41:40,602
and immediately after he sat,

1233
00:41:40,742 --> 00:41:43,742
he held up a blue case and opened it.

1234
00:41:44,342 --> 00:41:47,071
It was just a brief moment.

1235
00:41:47,072 --> 00:41:49,682
- In slow motion.
- But that moment went so slowly.

1236
00:41:50,312 --> 00:41:52,812
The case opened,

1237
00:41:53,182 --> 00:41:55,222
and there was a flash of light.

1238
00:41:56,422 --> 00:41:58,422
Is it that one?

1239
00:41:58,592 --> 00:42:00,992
- Is it that one?
- It's this one.

1240
00:42:01,092 --> 00:42:02,461
Is it this one?

1241
00:42:02,462 --> 00:42:03,921
(Her smile shines even though she covers her mouth.)

1242
00:42:03,922 --> 00:42:05,561
- I'm tearing up.
- Let me do it as well.

1243
00:42:05,562 --> 00:42:06,562
(Laughing)

1244
00:42:06,563 --> 00:42:09,362
- I might seem materialistic, - Let me do it as well.

1245
00:42:09,432 --> 00:42:12,071
- She's cute.
- I mean, you were getting married.

1246
00:42:12,072 --> 00:42:14,272
There really was...

1247
00:42:14,472 --> 00:42:16,942
a flash of light. Seriously.

1248
00:42:17,342 --> 00:42:19,072
It opened,

1249
00:42:19,742 --> 00:42:20,912
and I said, "Husband!"

1250
00:42:21,742 --> 00:42:23,741
- Did you smile in joy like that?
- You must have been happy.

1251
00:42:23,742 --> 00:42:26,251
My lips were smiling, and my eyes were tearing.

1252
00:42:26,252 --> 00:42:28,981
- Really?
- It was really touching.

1253
00:42:28,982 --> 00:42:30,422
(You should have told me before.)

1254
00:42:30,522 --> 00:42:32,022
(I'm so shocked.)

1255
00:42:32,492 --> 00:42:35,122
(Tears of happiness)

1256
00:42:35,322 --> 00:42:38,131
(Trying on her wedding ring for the first time)

1257
00:42:38,132 --> 00:42:40,932
(Trying on her wedding ring for the first time)

1258
00:42:41,132 --> 00:42:42,462
(Thank you.)

1259
00:42:42,662 --> 00:42:46,731
(Like that, they vowed to be together forever.)

1260
00:42:46,732 --> 00:42:49,771
I heard you talked about getting married first.

1261
00:42:49,772 --> 00:42:50,911
I said it first.

1262
00:42:50,912 --> 00:42:52,111
- Well done.
- Right.

1263
00:42:52,112 --> 00:42:53,312
You should marry a good person.

1264
00:42:53,512 --> 00:42:54,741
- That's cool.
- Right.

1265
00:42:54,742 --> 00:42:56,912
It seemed like he wanted to get married...

1266
00:42:57,082 --> 00:42:58,082
but couldn't get it...

1267
00:42:58,083 --> 00:42:59,881
- out of his mouth.
- You could feel that.

1268
00:42:59,882 --> 00:43:00,882
I could feel it.

1269
00:43:00,883 --> 00:43:02,552
So, on our way home, I asked,

1270
00:43:02,782 --> 00:43:04,651
"Should we get married?"

1271
00:43:04,652 --> 00:43:06,491
- Really?
- You just asked.

1272
00:43:06,492 --> 00:43:07,621
- Just like that?
- What did he say?

1273
00:43:07,622 --> 00:43:08,892
He said,

1274
00:43:09,192 --> 00:43:10,561
"When are you free?"

1275
00:43:10,562 --> 00:43:12,692
"Let's get married when you're free."

1276
00:43:13,092 --> 00:43:14,761
- So...
- That line...

1277
00:43:14,762 --> 00:43:18,501
- That line.
- The more I listen to it, it's...

1278
00:43:18,502 --> 00:43:19,671
- It's...
- But...

1279
00:43:19,672 --> 00:43:20,701
You can't tell...

1280
00:43:20,702 --> 00:43:23,101
- a beautiful story here.
- That's not true.

1281
00:43:23,102 --> 00:43:24,671
- It's because...
- Should I tell you about our fight?

1282
00:43:24,672 --> 00:43:26,741
I told Dong Hee that I completely understand.

1283
00:43:26,742 --> 00:43:29,341
- Your husband is like me.
- You can understand, right?

1284
00:43:29,342 --> 00:43:30,781
- Just stay quiet.
- I mean...

1285
00:43:30,782 --> 00:43:32,212
- We believe you.
- Why?

1286
00:43:32,652 --> 00:43:33,751
- "When are you free?"
- But if you say that the wrong way,

1287
00:43:33,752 --> 00:43:34,851
you can get seriously scolded.

1288
00:43:34,852 --> 00:43:36,021
It doesn't come out like that.

1289
00:43:36,022 --> 00:43:37,181
- Now...
- That's right.

1290
00:43:37,182 --> 00:43:38,852
What if he was a grumpy person?

1291
00:43:39,022 --> 00:43:40,652
"Okay. Let's get married when you're free."

1292
00:43:41,292 --> 00:43:42,462
"When I'm free?"

1293
00:43:42,822 --> 00:43:44,631
- "Alone?"
- "Are you kidding?"

1294
00:43:44,632 --> 00:43:46,231
That's possible.

1295
00:43:46,232 --> 00:43:47,802
- She could have said that.
-That can happen.

1296
00:43:48,332 --> 00:43:50,332
- "When I'm free?"
- That's possible.

1297
00:43:50,902 --> 00:43:53,502
Among the stages of marriage,

1298
00:43:53,732 --> 00:43:55,471
I think this is the hardest stage.

1299
00:43:55,472 --> 00:43:57,842
It's the wedding preparations.

1300
00:43:58,012 --> 00:43:59,511
- There are couples...
- Seriously.

1301
00:43:59,512 --> 00:44:00,981
Who break up during the preparations.

1302
00:44:00,982 --> 00:44:02,041
- That's right.
- We've heard about that a lot.

1303
00:44:02,042 --> 00:44:04,912
Did you ever fight during the preparations?

1304
00:44:05,182 --> 00:44:06,281
You wouldn't have fought.

1305
00:44:06,282 --> 00:44:09,782
I think wedding ceremonies should disappear.

1306
00:44:10,052 --> 00:44:11,992
- Why?
- It really gives you PTSD.

1307
00:44:12,452 --> 00:44:13,952
- Seriously.
- After taking all the time?

1308
00:44:14,052 --> 00:44:16,721
Starting from the invitation. The wedding ceremony...

1309
00:44:16,722 --> 00:44:19,492
- is just a show on its own.
- That's right.

1310
00:44:19,592 --> 00:44:21,501
I have to be the director, writer,

1311
00:44:21,502 --> 00:44:23,301
- and also the casting director.
- That's right.

1312
00:44:23,302 --> 00:44:24,401
That drives you crazy.

1313
00:44:24,402 --> 00:44:26,271
You also have to have a meal...

1314
00:44:26,272 --> 00:44:29,571
with 500 people at once.

1315
00:44:29,572 --> 00:44:31,471
- You have to plan all that.
- It drives you crazy.

1316
00:44:31,472 --> 00:44:32,711
- That's right.
- If you think of it as a show,

1317
00:44:32,712 --> 00:44:33,971
in Ho Dong's perspective,

1318
00:44:33,972 --> 00:44:35,442
you have no right to be tired!

1319
00:44:36,242 --> 00:44:38,182
You shouldn't get tired at your wedding!

1320
00:44:38,612 --> 00:44:40,052
- You have no right to be tired!
- Right.

1321
00:44:40,482 --> 00:44:41,781
- You shouldn't think like that.
- It's the 20th meal for me...

1322
00:44:41,782 --> 00:44:43,081
but it's one meal for others.

1323
00:44:43,082 --> 00:44:44,222
It's the first meal.

1324
00:44:44,792 --> 00:44:46,991
You have to have a professional mindset.

1325
00:44:46,992 --> 00:44:49,162
- But...
- Right. Those people made time...

1326
00:44:49,262 --> 00:44:50,692
- to come and congratulate you.
- Yes.

1327
00:44:50,892 --> 00:44:52,631
- I mean...
- You have no right to be tired.

1328
00:44:52,632 --> 00:44:54,361
You have a cheering team...

1329
00:44:54,362 --> 00:44:56,701
who could help you without getting paid.

1330
00:44:56,702 --> 00:44:58,931
That's right. Without them,

1331
00:44:58,932 --> 00:45:00,502
I wouldn't even have managed to make the wedding invitations.

1332
00:45:00,572 --> 00:45:01,671
They all came right?

1333
00:45:01,672 --> 00:45:03,001
- They all came.
- They would have.

1334
00:45:03,002 --> 00:45:04,102
- Right.
- Seriously.

1335
00:45:04,342 --> 00:45:06,971
- It would have been a great help.
- I made a fuss.

1336
00:45:06,972 --> 00:45:09,242
Now that I was getting married,

1337
00:45:09,342 --> 00:45:11,312
there were things I wanted to do.

1338
00:45:11,482 --> 00:45:14,421
At first, I was just going to make the wedding invitations.

1339
00:45:14,422 --> 00:45:16,451
But things escalated.

1340
00:45:16,452 --> 00:45:19,452
I even made custom scents.

1341
00:45:20,322 --> 00:45:21,862
I made a scented sachet.

1342
00:45:22,192 --> 00:45:24,832
I put them in the wedding invitations as a gift.

1343
00:45:24,992 --> 00:45:26,761
I ordered them, and they came.

1344
00:45:26,762 --> 00:45:28,031
But it was so hard...

1345
00:45:28,032 --> 00:45:29,301
- to assemble them.
- Right.

1346
00:45:29,302 --> 00:45:31,501
So I called my siblings.

1347
00:45:31,502 --> 00:45:32,531
- You asked them to come.
- I asked,

1348
00:45:32,532 --> 00:45:33,972
"Could you fold some papers for me?"

1349
00:45:34,172 --> 00:45:36,401
So they all came and we made the invitations.

1350
00:45:36,402 --> 00:45:38,472
So I managed to send the invitations.

1351
00:45:39,512 --> 00:45:42,582
(They joined hands, and they finished it in no time.)

1352
00:45:43,012 --> 00:45:45,082
People all have different personalities.

1353
00:45:45,382 --> 00:45:46,981
Indian people tend to be very spirited.

1354
00:45:46,982 --> 00:45:48,082
We're very spirited.

1355
00:45:48,482 --> 00:45:50,881
They tend to make every process fun.

1356
00:45:50,882 --> 00:45:53,491
- Of course.
- I had a hard time preparing,

1357
00:45:53,492 --> 00:45:55,562
but the process itself...

1358
00:45:55,762 --> 00:45:57,462
brought me so much joy.

1359
00:45:58,232 --> 00:46:00,662
The wedding day is a special day for me,

1360
00:46:00,792 --> 00:46:03,432
- but especially for a woman.
- Right.

1361
00:46:03,662 --> 00:46:05,071
So at first,

1362
00:46:05,072 --> 00:46:06,231
we wanted to invite 50 people...

1363
00:46:06,232 --> 00:46:08,201
and make it a small wedding.

1364
00:46:08,202 --> 00:46:10,242
But we moved from 50 people to 100 people in 1 day.

1365
00:46:10,772 --> 00:46:12,141
- Right.
- We thought about 50 people,

1366
00:46:12,142 --> 00:46:14,742
but when we added the wives and children, it became 100.

1367
00:46:14,912 --> 00:46:16,811
Then 100 people became 200.

1368
00:46:16,812 --> 00:46:19,582
You really have to edit the wedding invitations well.

1369
00:46:19,782 --> 00:46:21,551
You have to decide who to send or not send very well.

1370
00:46:21,552 --> 00:46:23,681
- It feels like "Squid Game."
- Right.

1371
00:46:23,682 --> 00:46:25,552
"Squid Game."

1372
00:46:26,092 --> 00:46:27,961
The most painful time...

1373
00:46:27,962 --> 00:46:29,821
If we compare it to an Indian wedding,

1374
00:46:29,822 --> 00:46:31,261
in Indian weddings,

1375
00:46:31,262 --> 00:46:33,491
you take pictures and go down to meet the people.

1376
00:46:33,492 --> 00:46:36,732
- The buffet is set up in a U-shape.
- You eat.

1377
00:46:37,002 --> 00:46:38,101
You eat...

1378
00:46:38,102 --> 00:46:40,531
- and mingle with the people.
- It's a nice system.

1379
00:46:40,532 --> 00:46:43,172
- That's nice.
- I've seen it in documentaries.

1380
00:46:43,542 --> 00:46:46,071
Indians greet, eat,

1381
00:46:46,072 --> 00:46:47,912
and then keep on dancing.

1382
00:46:48,012 --> 00:46:49,812
- For hours.
- Seriously.

1383
00:46:50,542 --> 00:46:53,181
- They dance until the next day.
- They dance throughout the day.

1384
00:46:53,182 --> 00:46:56,022
It's a free setting.

1385
00:46:56,252 --> 00:46:57,792
Even if you call 1,000 people,

1386
00:46:57,922 --> 00:47:00,022
- you don't feel pressured.
- Right. It goes on for days.

1387
00:47:00,222 --> 00:47:03,322
In Korea, you have to be punctual.

1388
00:47:03,622 --> 00:47:04,831
- The number should be 200...
- Right.

1389
00:47:04,832 --> 00:47:06,061
- or 300.
- Right. For the meals.

1390
00:47:06,062 --> 00:47:07,062
They give you...

1391
00:47:07,063 --> 00:47:08,262
- plus or minus 10 percent.
- That's right.

1392
00:47:08,432 --> 00:47:10,331
- That was really...
- We...

1393
00:47:10,332 --> 00:47:13,302
Did you have dancing at your wedding?

1394
00:47:13,472 --> 00:47:14,771
- We danced.
- Really?

1395
00:47:14,772 --> 00:47:16,002
- We danced.
- I missed that.

1396
00:47:16,272 --> 00:47:17,771
- It was an Indian wedding.
- I was invited, but I couldn't go.

1397
00:47:17,772 --> 00:47:20,141
(He added some Indian style.)

1398
00:47:20,142 --> 00:47:21,411
- Jeong Soo.
- Yes.

1399
00:47:21,412 --> 00:47:23,641
When you send out wedding invitations,

1400
00:47:23,642 --> 00:47:27,351
- how do you set the guest list?
- I didn't really have...

1401
00:47:27,352 --> 00:47:29,352
a standard.

1402
00:47:29,652 --> 00:47:31,652
I just thought I should go in alphabetical order.

1403
00:47:31,992 --> 00:47:34,192
So it went to Kang Ho Dong first.

1404
00:47:34,292 --> 00:47:35,721
(Kang has the priority even among K.)

1405
00:47:35,722 --> 00:47:38,662
I did it like that,

1406
00:47:38,862 --> 00:47:41,231
- and the number kept increasing.
- Right.

1407
00:47:41,232 --> 00:47:42,661
- So, - That's what happens.

1408
00:47:42,662 --> 00:47:44,232
I stopped at "S."

1409
00:47:44,432 --> 00:47:46,572
- What do you do then?
- Is that why it didn't come to me?

1410
00:47:46,772 --> 00:47:48,641
- Shin Dong!
- It stopped at "S."

1411
00:47:48,642 --> 00:47:50,441
- You didn't...
- I'm Hee Chul.

1412
00:47:50,442 --> 00:47:52,071
People with names starting with "H" can't get it.

1413
00:47:52,072 --> 00:47:53,841
- I couldn't get it...
- Your name starts...

1414
00:47:53,842 --> 00:47:55,581
- because my name starts with "H."
- with "H." Hee Chul.

1415
00:47:55,582 --> 00:47:58,111
But it came to me.

1416
00:47:58,112 --> 00:48:00,081
- It went to "Seo."
- His is "Shin."

1417
00:48:00,082 --> 00:48:02,081
- It made it to "Seo."
- Right.

1418
00:48:02,082 --> 00:48:03,881
- Right. So, - It didn't make it to "Shin."

1419
00:48:03,882 --> 00:48:05,621
I thought that wasn't going to work.

1420
00:48:05,622 --> 00:48:08,122
I thought, since I'm still a celebrity,

1421
00:48:08,462 --> 00:48:10,321
I should focus on inviting...

1422
00:48:10,322 --> 00:48:12,231
- the celebrities.
- Your colleagues.

1423
00:48:12,232 --> 00:48:13,391
That's what I thought.

1424
00:48:13,392 --> 00:48:15,562
But there were many people who couldn't make it on that day.

1425
00:48:15,732 --> 00:48:16,862
Right.

1426
00:48:17,202 --> 00:48:18,801
- They found out on that day.
- Asking them in advance...

1427
00:48:18,802 --> 00:48:20,031
is meaningless.

1428
00:48:20,032 --> 00:48:23,242
So I wanted to say this here today.

1429
00:48:23,872 --> 00:48:25,342
Kim Yeong Cheol did well.

1430
00:48:25,542 --> 00:48:26,571
- Why?
- He told me he couldn't come...

1431
00:48:26,572 --> 00:48:27,572
in advance.

1432
00:48:27,573 --> 00:48:29,681
His spot could be given out to someone else.

1433
00:48:29,682 --> 00:48:31,451
- I sent the congratulatory money.
- He gave me a large amount.

1434
00:48:31,452 --> 00:48:32,482
Okay.

1435
00:48:32,612 --> 00:48:34,312
Kang Ho Dong came.

1436
00:48:35,022 --> 00:48:38,292
He gave me a large sum befitting his name.

1437
00:48:38,422 --> 00:48:41,092
So I thank you once again.

1438
00:48:41,692 --> 00:48:44,091
- Oh, pass. And then?
- Okay, keep going 1 by 1.

1439
00:48:44,092 --> 00:48:45,161
- And?
- Next?

1440
00:48:45,162 --> 00:48:46,192
- Lee Soo Geun!
- What?

1441
00:48:47,492 --> 00:48:50,462
How could you call me and say that you can't come on the wedding day?

1442
00:48:50,732 --> 00:48:52,231
- Wasn't it the day before?
- That's mean.

1443
00:48:52,232 --> 00:48:54,272
Hey, 12am on the night before is the day of.

1444
00:48:55,642 --> 00:48:57,101
- Good job.
- I called the night before.

1445
00:48:57,102 --> 00:48:58,571
So, Soo Geun's seat...

1446
00:48:58,572 --> 00:49:00,441
was emptied in a rush. There's no way for me to know...

1447
00:49:00,442 --> 00:49:01,511
if someone else filled the seat or not.

1448
00:49:01,512 --> 00:49:02,912
- It was at the last minute.
- Whether someone filled it or not.

1449
00:49:03,042 --> 00:49:04,381
- Next...
- Lee Sang Min.

1450
00:49:04,382 --> 00:49:06,752
- I'm most curious about Sang Min.
- What? Why?

1451
00:49:06,782 --> 00:49:09,221
- I texted Lee Sang Min.
- Right.

1452
00:49:09,222 --> 00:49:11,192
But he read the message and never replied.

1453
00:49:11,252 --> 00:49:12,891
- He ignored you?
- So, I thought,

1454
00:49:12,892 --> 00:49:15,362
"Sang Min must not be able to come." Or so I thought.

1455
00:49:15,562 --> 00:49:17,261
- But then, he came!
- Did you go for a free meal?

1456
00:49:17,262 --> 00:49:19,591
- Come on. What?
- Hey, that's good, though.

1457
00:49:19,592 --> 00:49:22,301
- Then, he'd be in Soo Geun's spot.
- Right.

1458
00:49:22,302 --> 00:49:25,271
But how do I get this message to the security guards?

1459
00:49:25,272 --> 00:49:26,771
- I'm standing at the front.
- It's the day of your wedding.

1460
00:49:26,772 --> 00:49:28,801
Of course, Sang Min left a big money gift.

1461
00:49:28,802 --> 00:49:30,801
- I was grateful, but...
- This story is entertaining.

1462
00:49:30,802 --> 00:49:33,241
No. This year, I was really exhausted...

1463
00:49:33,242 --> 00:49:35,781
from all the weddings.

1464
00:49:35,782 --> 00:49:37,911
- Is that so?
- It was okay in the first half,

1465
00:49:37,912 --> 00:49:39,311
until about June or July.

1466
00:49:39,312 --> 00:49:42,021
Gosh, when I saw the invitations continuing to flood in after August?

1467
00:49:42,022 --> 00:49:44,622
- Gosh, it was seriously...
- Okay. I've heard enough.

1468
00:49:45,052 --> 00:49:46,621
Okay, I've heard enough.

1469
00:49:46,622 --> 00:49:47,721
- That's what he does!
- Anyway.

1470
00:49:47,722 --> 00:49:48,761
(Nice timing)

1471
00:49:48,762 --> 00:49:50,891
- How funny.
- Anyway.

1472
00:49:50,892 --> 00:49:52,831
- Anyway!
- You came...

1473
00:49:52,832 --> 00:49:54,361
- and left a money gift.
- He cut him off.

1474
00:49:54,362 --> 00:49:55,931
- Next, Jang Hoon.
- Yes.

1475
00:49:55,932 --> 00:49:58,772
He said he wouldn't be able to come, so he sent me a money gift before.

1476
00:49:59,032 --> 00:50:00,201
- As for Kyung Hoon, - Probably a lot.

1477
00:50:00,202 --> 00:50:01,401
I didn't have his number.

1478
00:50:01,402 --> 00:50:03,871
- So...
- Hey, he's so mean.

1479
00:50:03,872 --> 00:50:06,841
- Why?
- You called to ask favors before.

1480
00:50:06,842 --> 00:50:08,881
- Yes, through my manager.
- Right.

1481
00:50:08,882 --> 00:50:10,211
- But why not...
- I thought it was too much...

1482
00:50:10,212 --> 00:50:11,452
to invite you through my manager.

1483
00:50:12,152 --> 00:50:13,152
- Hee Chul...
- Did you not invite me...

1484
00:50:13,152 --> 00:50:14,152
since my name is at the end of the Korean alphabet?

1485
00:50:14,153 --> 00:50:16,481
I thought Hee Chul would cause chaos if he came,

1486
00:50:16,482 --> 00:50:17,921
so I crossed him off the list.

1487
00:50:17,922 --> 00:50:19,451
You know, I'd definitely do this.

1488
00:50:19,452 --> 00:50:21,321
When I receive a wedding invitation online,

1489
00:50:21,322 --> 00:50:22,391
I always send a money gift...

1490
00:50:22,392 --> 00:50:23,421
- even if I can't go.
- Of course.

1491
00:50:23,422 --> 00:50:24,591
- I send a money gift for sure.
- Right.

1492
00:50:24,592 --> 00:50:25,991
- But we also...
- It's still not too late.

1493
00:50:25,992 --> 00:50:27,331
- We were abroad.
- They were abroad.

1494
00:50:27,332 --> 00:50:29,702
- Gosh, that's so funny.
- I wanted to invite everyone too.

1495
00:50:30,132 --> 00:50:33,131
I sent an invitation to Sang Min.

1496
00:50:33,132 --> 00:50:35,172
You totally ignored it after you read it.

1497
00:50:35,872 --> 00:50:38,411
- But...
- Why, that...

1498
00:50:38,412 --> 00:50:40,071
- Why did you do that?
- Why would you read and ignore it?

1499
00:50:40,072 --> 00:50:41,781
- Explain yourself!
- But you know...

1500
00:50:41,782 --> 00:50:44,042
Sang Min came to my house once for a different shoot.

1501
00:50:44,282 --> 00:50:45,911
- He even came to your house?
- He came to my house...

1502
00:50:45,912 --> 00:50:49,051
and was like, "Hey, I bought a house in a nearby area."

1503
00:50:49,052 --> 00:50:52,021
"I'll come to your wedding and give you a gift." But then...

1504
00:50:52,022 --> 00:50:53,891
- You were on the same show, - I know he's so busy, though.

1505
00:50:53,892 --> 00:50:54,961
And you knew,

1506
00:50:54,962 --> 00:50:56,892
- but you read and ignored his text?
- Well...

1507
00:50:58,362 --> 00:51:01,862
- So...
- Okay, I've heard enough.

1508
00:51:03,302 --> 00:51:05,971
- He didn't say anything.
- You know...

1509
00:51:05,972 --> 00:51:07,941
- Yes, that's enough.
- That's so funny.

1510
00:51:07,942 --> 00:51:09,601
- Good job.
- Sang Min can't say a word.

1511
00:51:09,602 --> 00:51:11,471
- "I've heard enough."
- I'm grateful for Hee Chul, though.

1512
00:51:11,472 --> 00:51:13,941
- I got an invitation.
- He's such a superstar.

1513
00:51:13,942 --> 00:51:16,542
He's so popular in India too.

1514
00:51:16,782 --> 00:51:19,381
- But he told me he couldn't come.
- Hee Chul is so nice.

1515
00:51:19,382 --> 00:51:22,122
- I'm just grateful for the call, - Yes, because of a concert.

1516
00:51:22,352 --> 00:51:25,291
But my goodness. He sent a huge money gift.

1517
00:51:25,292 --> 00:51:27,091
- I was so... Seriously, thank you.
- Indeed.

1518
00:51:27,092 --> 00:51:29,091
If I can't make it, I always... We all give big money gifts.

1519
00:51:29,092 --> 00:51:30,291
- I see.
- Right.

1520
00:51:30,292 --> 00:51:32,191
Money... I'm pretty sure the invitations...

1521
00:51:32,192 --> 00:51:34,262
stay online with the bank account information for a few weeks or so.

1522
00:51:35,462 --> 00:51:37,661
- Is it still available online?
- Yes, it is.

1523
00:51:37,662 --> 00:51:39,831
- They last for 3 months.
- Up to 3 months?

1524
00:51:39,832 --> 00:51:42,201
- They stay available for so long.
- There's no way to escape it.

1525
00:51:42,202 --> 00:51:43,301
- He's funny.
- No way.

1526
00:51:43,302 --> 00:51:45,511
I heard Ha Na's wedding was very touching.

1527
00:51:45,512 --> 00:51:46,942
- Do we have a video?
- Oh, it was?

1528
00:51:47,642 --> 00:51:50,712
(Ha Na, a bride in pure white)

1529
00:51:51,582 --> 00:51:53,251
- With your grandma.
- Oh, with your grandma?

1530
00:51:53,252 --> 00:51:54,481
Grandma.

1531
00:51:54,482 --> 00:51:57,052
- I walked down the aisle with her.
- She looks so healthy.

1532
00:51:58,052 --> 00:51:59,951
My grandma is over 90 years old.

1533
00:51:59,952 --> 00:52:01,721
- This is making me tear up.
- Gosh, she's so healthy.

1534
00:52:01,722 --> 00:52:03,591
You did a great thing by getting married when she's still healthy.

1535
00:52:03,592 --> 00:52:06,891
My grandma pretty much raised me.

1536
00:52:06,892 --> 00:52:10,461
We weren't sure if Grandma would be able to come that day,

1537
00:52:10,462 --> 00:52:13,931
but thankfully, she felt up to it and was able to come.

1538
00:52:13,932 --> 00:52:15,441
We couldn't do a rehearsal with her,

1539
00:52:15,442 --> 00:52:17,771
because she has...

1540
00:52:17,772 --> 00:52:19,441
a cute case of dementia.

1541
00:52:19,442 --> 00:52:23,042
Sometimes, she recognizes me, and sometimes, she doesn't.

1542
00:52:23,182 --> 00:52:24,811
So, originally, I thought...

1543
00:52:24,812 --> 00:52:27,081
it'd be nice to walk down the aisle with my mother-in-law and husband.

1544
00:52:27,082 --> 00:52:29,651
I wanted to do something eventful like that,

1545
00:52:29,652 --> 00:52:32,391
but on the day of, I asked my grandma at the salon.

1546
00:52:32,392 --> 00:52:34,761
I asked her, "Grandma, will you be okay?" And she seemed...

1547
00:52:34,762 --> 00:52:36,721
to be very alert that day.

1548
00:52:36,722 --> 00:52:39,191
So, we decided it on the day of, and we walked down the aisle.

1549
00:52:39,192 --> 00:52:40,791
I'm sure my grandma didn't know.

1550
00:52:40,792 --> 00:52:43,231
- So, we walked in together, - That's good.

1551
00:52:43,232 --> 00:52:44,931
And she did so well.

1552
00:52:44,932 --> 00:52:46,602
So, my aunt said the same thing.

1553
00:52:47,132 --> 00:52:50,802
"Hurry up and get married while we're still young and beautiful."

1554
00:52:51,002 --> 00:52:53,071
Family elders would tell me this.

1555
00:52:53,072 --> 00:52:55,381
They want to look pretty in the wedding photos.

1556
00:52:55,382 --> 00:52:57,081
- Right.
- So, those who marry early...

1557
00:52:57,082 --> 00:52:59,451
- seem so great to me.
- For real.

1558
00:52:59,452 --> 00:53:01,521
Hey, Lucky. I've heard about this.

1559
00:53:01,522 --> 00:53:03,451
Having a wedding in Korea and another one abroad.

1560
00:53:03,452 --> 00:53:06,092
Then, shouldn't you have a wedding in India too?

1561
00:53:06,152 --> 00:53:08,021
If I had gotten married 20 years ago,

1562
00:53:08,022 --> 00:53:09,491
that would've been nice.

1563
00:53:09,492 --> 00:53:12,331
But now, my family in India is so big.

1564
00:53:12,332 --> 00:53:15,462
Also, you can't have a wedding in just a few hours in India.

1565
00:53:15,802 --> 00:53:17,901
In order to get married, you need a week, at least.

1566
00:53:17,902 --> 00:53:18,902
What?

1567
00:53:19,572 --> 00:53:22,202
- A week?
- That's on a whole different scale.

1568
00:53:22,602 --> 00:53:23,741
- This is...
- A week?

1569
00:53:23,742 --> 00:53:25,941
- This is a joke in India.
- Can you seriously do that?

1570
00:53:25,942 --> 00:53:27,641
Why don't people get divorced in India?

1571
00:53:27,642 --> 00:53:30,541
With our wedding process, you just can't get divorced.

1572
00:53:30,542 --> 00:53:31,911
- Totally.
- Of course you can't.

1573
00:53:31,912 --> 00:53:33,151
- For a week.
- It's a whole week.

1574
00:53:33,152 --> 00:53:35,551
So, it would be nice to do so, but...

1575
00:53:35,552 --> 00:53:36,581
A week.

1576
00:53:36,582 --> 00:53:37,821
After the wedding,

1577
00:53:37,822 --> 00:53:39,021
- we went to India.
- You visited?

1578
00:53:39,022 --> 00:53:41,221
It was also a big holiday in India called Diwali.

1579
00:53:41,222 --> 00:53:42,591
We went for the holidays.

1580
00:53:42,592 --> 00:53:44,931
(Dawali: Between late October to early November each year)

1581
00:53:44,932 --> 00:53:47,292
(The largest holiday in Hinduism, it means beating darkness with light.)

1582
00:53:47,432 --> 00:53:48,801
We said hello to my mom...

1583
00:53:48,802 --> 00:53:50,461
and stuff like that.

1584
00:53:50,462 --> 00:53:52,031
- Right.
- But for my wife,

1585
00:53:52,032 --> 00:53:53,631
she would've had a fantasy...

1586
00:53:53,632 --> 00:53:55,301
about an Indian wedding and whatnot.

1587
00:53:55,302 --> 00:53:57,801
So, we went to the most famous wedding designer in India.

1588
00:53:57,802 --> 00:53:59,641
At the designer's shop,

1589
00:53:59,642 --> 00:54:01,711
we wore traditional wedding outfits,

1590
00:54:01,712 --> 00:54:02,941
- and we had a photoshoot.
- Did you?

1591
00:54:02,942 --> 00:54:04,581
- Just photos.
- Right.

1592
00:54:04,582 --> 00:54:05,811
- That's good.
- That's awesome.

1593
00:54:05,812 --> 00:54:07,251
Gosh, that's so fancy.

1594
00:54:07,252 --> 00:54:08,352
How pretty.

1595
00:54:08,622 --> 00:54:10,181
- That's cool.
- That's the designer's shop?

1596
00:54:10,182 --> 00:54:13,151
I'm pretty sure that outfit alone weighs about 25kg.

1597
00:54:13,152 --> 00:54:14,422
- It weighs 25kg?
- What?

1598
00:54:14,522 --> 00:54:16,021
It takes about six months to make,

1599
00:54:16,022 --> 00:54:18,732
and it costs over 30,000 dollars.

1600
00:54:19,462 --> 00:54:21,331
- For 30,000 dollars...
- It's so expensive.

1601
00:54:21,332 --> 00:54:24,061
The hanbok for my wedding was made by Designer Park Sul Nyeo too.

1602
00:54:24,062 --> 00:54:26,401
- They were so beautiful.
- Right, Designer Park Sul Nyeo.

1603
00:54:26,402 --> 00:54:28,641
- Her hanboks are so amazing.
- I was so grateful.

1604
00:54:28,642 --> 00:54:31,841
Yes, it was good for your wife that you only did the photoshoot.

1605
00:54:31,842 --> 00:54:33,811
- Most importantly, she's pregnant.
- What if all that dancing...

1606
00:54:33,812 --> 00:54:35,941
- Yes, right.
- She's pregnant.

1607
00:54:35,942 --> 00:54:37,781
- That would've been too hard.
- To dance for a week?

1608
00:54:37,782 --> 00:54:40,152
- No, you could never do that.
- Of course not. It's no joke.

1609
00:54:40,212 --> 00:54:42,751
I'm sure your parents knew that and gave their blessing too.

1610
00:54:42,752 --> 00:54:45,251
Bo Ra, when you were looking for a wedding venue,

1611
00:54:45,252 --> 00:54:47,521
why did you focus so much on the waiting room?

1612
00:54:47,522 --> 00:54:50,161
Usually, brides focus on...

1613
00:54:50,162 --> 00:54:51,991
the aisle and stuff like that.

1614
00:54:51,992 --> 00:54:54,261
But since I have such a huge family,

1615
00:54:54,262 --> 00:54:56,031
the family waiting room was...

1616
00:54:56,032 --> 00:54:59,501
They were all made for families of four.

1617
00:54:59,502 --> 00:55:00,671
- That's so funny.
- Are they mostly made for four?

1618
00:55:00,672 --> 00:55:03,371
Yes! So, when we would go on tours of the wedding halls,

1619
00:55:03,372 --> 00:55:05,011
we made sure to ask,

1620
00:55:05,012 --> 00:55:06,671
"How many people can the waiting room hold?"

1621
00:55:06,672 --> 00:55:09,312
"Can it hold ten people?"

1622
00:55:09,442 --> 00:55:12,111
So, when my whole family was together...

1623
00:55:12,112 --> 00:55:13,112
And we have to count...

1624
00:55:13,113 --> 00:55:14,482
- my in-laws' family too.
- Of course.

1625
00:55:14,612 --> 00:55:16,682
There were 22 of us on the move that day.

1626
00:55:17,482 --> 00:55:18,751
- It must feel so reassuring.
- That's just the immediate family.

1627
00:55:18,752 --> 00:55:20,691
But you have to get your hair and makeup done on the day of.

1628
00:55:20,692 --> 00:55:22,021
It was a huge ordeal, seriously.

1629
00:55:22,022 --> 00:55:23,561
And clothes too.

1630
00:55:23,562 --> 00:55:26,762
Right, so this is practically the same as a Super Junior show.

1631
00:55:27,092 --> 00:55:28,261
- Super Junior...
- True.

1632
00:55:28,262 --> 00:55:30,501
- Hey, I totally get it now.
- Right?

1633
00:55:30,502 --> 00:55:32,001
- I mean...
- We go to three different salons.

1634
00:55:32,002 --> 00:55:33,171
- Yes. For 13 members, - We have 3 makeup salons.

1635
00:55:33,172 --> 00:55:34,801
- you go to 3 salons, right?
- We go to 3 salons.

1636
00:55:34,802 --> 00:55:36,271
We also went to three salons.

1637
00:55:36,272 --> 00:55:37,742
- Hey, but...
- You couldn't all go to one place?

1638
00:55:37,802 --> 00:55:39,311
Next, and this is very important.

1639
00:55:39,312 --> 00:55:41,511
There are things that change after you get married.

1640
00:55:41,512 --> 00:55:43,381
- There are changes, because...
- Like moving?

1641
00:55:43,382 --> 00:55:44,382
You live apart before,

1642
00:55:44,383 --> 00:55:45,551
- and then, you have to move.
- Right.

1643
00:55:45,552 --> 00:55:47,151
You move into the same place. How is it?

1644
00:55:47,152 --> 00:55:49,321
Once you move in and start living together,

1645
00:55:49,322 --> 00:55:50,821
- I think that part will be so hard.
- how is it?

1646
00:55:50,822 --> 00:55:52,491
- Is it hard?
- You wake up, and someone is there.

1647
00:55:52,492 --> 00:55:53,692
- It's uncomfortable.
- It's so...

1648
00:55:53,922 --> 00:55:55,291
I'd feel careful about using the bathroom too.

1649
00:55:55,292 --> 00:55:56,761
How is it, Jeong Soo?

1650
00:55:56,762 --> 00:56:00,032
- Jeong Soo is very neat too.
- Can I speak after I hear them?

1651
00:56:00,632 --> 00:56:01,961
- Oh, nice one.
- Hey.

1652
00:56:01,962 --> 00:56:04,002
- I might have to dial it down.
- Okay.

1653
00:56:04,532 --> 00:56:07,271
- He's so careful around people.
- Get your head on straight today.

1654
00:56:07,272 --> 00:56:09,501
- I don't want to go on your show.
- Get your head in the game.

1655
00:56:09,502 --> 00:56:11,812
So, let me dial it down a bit if I have to.

1656
00:56:12,112 --> 00:56:13,611
- What about you, Bo Ra?
- Gosh, that's cute.

1657
00:56:13,612 --> 00:56:15,012
I honestly love it so much.

1658
00:56:15,382 --> 00:56:16,681
I love it.

1659
00:56:16,682 --> 00:56:19,951
Sometimes, living together with my husband...

1660
00:56:19,952 --> 00:56:21,251
"Is this real?"

1661
00:56:21,252 --> 00:56:22,621
"We're living together."

1662
00:56:22,622 --> 00:56:23,821
"We'll live together..."

1663
00:56:23,822 --> 00:56:24,991
- "for our whole lives."
- You must be a good match.

1664
00:56:24,992 --> 00:56:26,351
Also, they say that when you get married,

1665
00:56:26,352 --> 00:56:28,121
you get into fights because you don't see eye to eye.

1666
00:56:28,122 --> 00:56:30,091
- It's the total opposite for me.
- Do you get along well?

1667
00:56:30,092 --> 00:56:33,661
- It's like I married my other self.
- You don't have reasons to fight?

1668
00:56:33,662 --> 00:56:34,901
- Your other self.
- Yes.

1669
00:56:34,902 --> 00:56:37,061
So, from the beginning,

1670
00:56:37,062 --> 00:56:38,771
we didn't want to fight...

1671
00:56:38,772 --> 00:56:40,231
and said, "Let's compromise, one thing at a time."

1672
00:56:40,232 --> 00:56:42,971
We went through that process.

1673
00:56:42,972 --> 00:56:45,571
Honestly, people start fighting over how to fold the laundry, you know?

1674
00:56:45,572 --> 00:56:47,311
So, we came to an agreement.

1675
00:56:47,312 --> 00:56:50,581
"How do you fold the laundry? This is how I do it."

1676
00:56:50,582 --> 00:56:53,181
"Shall we do it this way?" We agreed on that first.

1677
00:56:53,182 --> 00:56:54,381
It's like you're playing house.

1678
00:56:54,382 --> 00:56:55,621
- That's nice.
- That's wise.

1679
00:56:55,622 --> 00:56:56,721
- You're a good match.
- For real.

1680
00:56:56,722 --> 00:56:58,751
Then, Ha Na, what about your parrot?

1681
00:56:58,752 --> 00:57:00,491
I was actually very worried.

1682
00:57:00,492 --> 00:57:03,991
What if my parrot bites my husband?

1683
00:57:03,992 --> 00:57:05,561
I was even worried...

1684
00:57:05,562 --> 00:57:09,101
that I might not be able to keep my pet if he bit my husband.

1685
00:57:09,102 --> 00:57:11,902
But thankfully, he only bites me, not my husband.

1686
00:57:12,472 --> 00:57:13,871
- His love has shifted.
- Oh, really?

1687
00:57:13,872 --> 00:57:15,341
- How is that possible?
- I've been pushed aside.

1688
00:57:15,342 --> 00:57:17,301
That's how well they get along.

1689
00:57:17,302 --> 00:57:18,871
- My husband is so gentle.
- That's good.

1690
00:57:18,872 --> 00:57:21,342
He helps out around the house as a given.

1691
00:57:21,542 --> 00:57:23,311
Maybe it's because he was a point guard,

1692
00:57:23,312 --> 00:57:24,312
he has a wide range of vision.

1693
00:57:24,313 --> 00:57:26,481
- If I...
- Because he's a point guard?

1694
00:57:26,482 --> 00:57:27,712
(A basketball player's range of vision is useful at home too.)

1695
00:57:27,952 --> 00:57:29,981
- He was a point guard.
- Does he see everything?

1696
00:57:29,982 --> 00:57:32,091
Park Ha Na is pretty much...

1697
00:57:32,092 --> 00:57:33,321
a basketball person now.

1698
00:57:33,322 --> 00:57:34,791
When do you feel that...

1699
00:57:34,792 --> 00:57:36,691
- he has a wide range of vision?
- So, I clean the house once.

1700
00:57:36,692 --> 00:57:38,432
If I clean the house in my own way,

1701
00:57:38,462 --> 00:57:40,091
my husband cleans it next time in the same way.

1702
00:57:40,092 --> 00:57:41,531
- Oh, he remembers it?
- So,

1703
00:57:41,532 --> 00:57:43,731
- when I ask him for help, - He's like a real parrot too.

1704
00:57:43,732 --> 00:57:45,301
- he's already doing it that way.
- Is he already doing it?

1705
00:57:45,302 --> 00:57:46,731
- We have no reason to fight.
- He must be quick.

1706
00:57:46,732 --> 00:57:47,931
- Right.
- No, we've never...

1707
00:57:47,932 --> 00:57:49,001
- fought before.
- He sounds very quick-witted.

1708
00:57:49,002 --> 00:57:50,002
- Not having reasons to fight...
